data_0005.name: Resource type
data_0005.definition: A type of computational resource used in bioinformatics.

data_0006.name: Data
data_0006.definition: Information, represented in an information artefact (data record) that is 'understandable' by dedicated computational tools that can use the data as input or produce it as output.

data_0007.name: Tool
data_0007.definition: A bioinformatics package or tool, e.g. a standalone application or web service.

data_0581.name: Database
data_0581.definition: A digital data archive typically based around a relational model but sometimes using an object-oriented, tree or graph-based model.

data_0582.name: Ontology
data_0582.definition: An ontology of biological or bioinformatics concepts and relations, a controlled vocabulary, structured glossary etc.

data_0583.name: Directory metadata
data_0583.definition: A directory on disk from which files are read.

data_0831.name: MeSH vocabulary
data_0831.definition: Controlled vocabulary from National Library of Medicine. The MeSH thesaurus is used to index articles in biomedical journals for the Medline/PubMED databases.

data_0832.name: HGNC vocabulary
data_0832.definition: Controlled vocabulary for gene names (symbols) from HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee.

data_0835.name: UMLS vocabulary
data_0835.definition: Compendium of controlled vocabularies for the biomedical domain (Unified Medical Language System).

data_0842.name: Identifier
data_0842.definition: A text token, number or something else which identifies an entity, but which may not be persistent (stable) or unique (the same identifier may identify multiple things).

data_0843.name: Database entry
data_0843.definition: An entry (retrievable via URL) from a biological database.

data_0846.name: Chemical formula
data_0846.definition: A specification of a chemical structure.

data_0847.name: QSAR descriptor
data_0847.definition:
A QSAR quantitative descriptor (name-value pair) of chemical structure.
QSAR descriptors have numeric values that quantify chemical information encoded in a symbolic representation of a molecule. They are used in quantitative structure activity relationship (QSAR) applications. Many subtypes of individual descriptors (not included in EDAM) cover various types of protein properties.

data_0848.name: Raw sequence
data_0848.definition:
A raw molecular sequence (string of characters) which might include ambiguity, unknown positions and non-sequence characters.
Non-sequence characters may be used for example for gaps and translation stop.

data_0849.name: Sequence record
data_0849.definition: A molecular sequence and associated metadata.

data_0850.name: Sequence set
data_0850.definition:
A collection of one or typically multiple molecular sequences (which can include derived data or metadata) that do not (typically) correspond to molecular sequence database records or entries and which (typically) are derived from some analytical method.
An example is an alignment reference; one or a set of reference molecular sequences, structures, or profiles used for alignment of genomic, transcriptomic, or proteomic experimental data.
This concept may be used for arbitrary sequence sets and associated data arising from processing.

data_0851.name: Sequence mask character
data_0851.definition: A character used to replace (mask) other characters in a molecular sequence.

data_0852.name: Sequence mask type
data_0852.definition:
A label (text token) describing the type of sequence masking to perform.
Sequence masking is where specific characters or positions in a molecular sequence are masked (replaced) with an another (mask character). The mask type indicates what is masked, for example regions that are not of interest or which are information-poor including acidic protein regions, basic protein regions, proline-rich regions, low compositional complexity regions, short-periodicity internal repeats, simple repeats and low complexity regions. Masked sequences are used in database search to eliminate statistically significant but biologically uninteresting hits.

data_0853.name: DNA sense specification
data_0853.definition:
The strand of a DNA sequence (forward or reverse).
The forward or 'top' strand might specify a sequence is to be used as given, the reverse or 'bottom' strand specifying the reverse complement of the sequence is to be used.

data_0855.name: Sequence metadata
data_0855.definition:
Basic or general information concerning molecular sequences.
This is used for such things as a report including the sequence identifier, type and length.

data_0856.name: Sequence feature source
data_0856.definition:
How the annotation of a sequence feature (for example in EMBL or Swiss-Prot) was derived.
This might be the name and version of a software tool, the name of a database, or 'curated' to indicate a manual annotation (made by a human).

data_0857.name: Sequence search results
data_0857.definition:
A report of sequence hits and associated data from searching a database of sequences (for example a BLAST search). This will typically include a list of scores (often with statistical evaluation) and a set of alignments for the hits.
The score list includes the alignment score, percentage of the query sequence matched, length of the database sequence entry in this alignment, identifier of the database sequence entry, excerpt of the database sequence entry description etc.

data_0858.name: Sequence signature matches
data_0858.definition:
Report on the location of matches ("hits") between sequences, sequence profiles, motifs (conserved or functional patterns) and other types of sequence signatures.
A "profile-profile alignment" is an alignment of two sequence profiles, each profile typically representing a sequence alignment.
This includes reports of hits from a search of a protein secondary or domain database. Data associated with the search or alignment might also be included, e.g. ranked list of best-scoring sequences, a graphical representation of scores etc.
A "sequence-profile alignment" is an alignment of one or more molecular sequence(s) to one or more sequence profile(s) (each profile typically representing a sequence alignment).

data_0859.name: Sequence signature model
data_0859.definition: Data files used by motif or profile methods.

data_0860.name: Sequence signature data
data_0860.definition:
Data concering concerning specific or conserved pattern in molecular sequences and the classifiers used for their identification, including sequence motifs, profiles or other diagnostic element.
This can include metadata about a motif or sequence profile such as its name, length, technical details about the profile construction, and so on.

data_0861.name: Sequence alignment (words)
data_0861.definition: Alignment of exact matches between subsequences (words) within two or more molecular sequences.

data_0862.name: Dotplot
data_0862.definition: A dotplot of sequence similarities identified from word-matching or character comparison.

data_0864.name: Sequence alignment parameter
data_0864.definition: Some simple value controlling a sequence alignment (or similar 'match') operation.

data_0865.name: Sequence similarity score
data_0865.definition: A value representing molecular sequence similarity.

data_0866.name: Sequence alignment metadata
data_0866.definition: Report of general information on a sequence alignment, typically include a description, sequence identifiers and alignment score.

data_0867.name: Sequence alignment report
data_0867.definition:
An informative report of molecular sequence alignment-derived data or metadata.
Use this for any computer-generated reports on sequence alignments, and for general information (metadata) on a sequence alignment, such as a description, sequence identifiers and alignment score.

data_0868.name: Profile-profile alignment
data_0868.definition: A profile-profile alignment (each profile typically representing a sequence alignment).

data_0869.name: Sequence-profile alignment
data_0869.definition: Alignment of one or more molecular sequence(s) to one or more sequence profile(s) (each profile typically representing a sequence alignment).

data_0870.name: Sequence distance matrix
data_0870.definition:
A matrix of estimated evolutionary distance between molecular sequences, such as is suitable for phylogenetic tree calculation.
Methods might perform character compatibility analysis or identify patterns of similarity in an alignment or data matrix.

data_0871.name: Phylogenetic character data
data_0871.definition:
Basic character data from which a phylogenetic tree may be generated.
As defined, this concept would also include molecular sequences, microsatellites, polymorphisms (RAPDs, RFLPs, or AFLPs), restriction sites and fragments

data_0872.name: Phylogenetic tree
data_0872.definition:
The raw data (not just an image) from which a phylogenetic tree is directly generated or plotted, such as topology, lengths (in time or in expected amounts of variance) and a confidence interval for each length.
A phylogenetic tree is usually constructed from a set of sequences from which an alignment (or data matrix) is calculated. See also 'Phylogenetic tree image'.

data_0874.name: Comparison matrix
data_0874.definition:
Matrix of integer or floating point numbers for amino acid or nucleotide sequence comparison.
The comparison matrix might include matrix name, optional comment, height and width (or size) of matrix, an index row/column (of characters) and data rows/columns (of integers or floats).

data_0875.name: Protein topology
data_0875.definition:
Predicted or actual protein topology represented as a string of protein secondary structure elements.
The location and size of the secondary structure elements and intervening loop regions is usually indicated.

data_0876.name: Protein features report (secondary structure)
data_0876.definition: Secondary structure (predicted or real) of a protein.

data_0877.name: Protein features report (super-secondary)
data_0877.definition:
Super-secondary structure of protein sequence(s).
Super-secondary structures include leucine zippers, coiled coils, Helix-Turn-Helix etc.

data_0878.name: Protein secondary structure alignment
data_0878.definition: Alignment of the (1D representations of) secondary structure of two or more proteins.

data_0879.name: Secondary structure alignment metadata (protein)
data_0879.definition: An informative report on protein secondary structure alignment-derived data or metadata.

data_0880.name: RNA secondary structure
data_0880.definition:
An informative report of secondary structure (predicted or real) of an RNA molecule.
This includes thermodynamically stable or evolutionarily conserved structures such as knots, pseudoknots etc.

data_0881.name: RNA secondary structure alignment
data_0881.definition: Alignment of the (1D representations of) secondary structure of two or more RNA molecules.

data_0882.name: Secondary structure alignment metadata (RNA)
data_0882.definition: An informative report of RNA secondary structure alignment-derived data or metadata.

data_0883.name: Structure
data_0883.definition:
3D coordinate and associated data for a macromolecular tertiary (3D) structure or part of a structure.
The coordinate data may be predicted or real.

data_0884.name: Tertiary structure record
data_0884.definition: An entry from a molecular tertiary (3D) structure database.

data_0885.name: Structure database search results
data_0885.definition: Results (hits) from searching a database of tertiary structure.

data_0886.name: Structure alignment
data_0886.definition:
Alignment (superimposition) of molecular tertiary (3D) structures.
A tertiary structure alignment will include the untransformed coordinates of one macromolecule, followed by the second (or subsequent) structure(s) with all the coordinates transformed (by rotation / translation) to give a superposition.

data_0887.name: Structure alignment report
data_0887.definition:
An informative report of molecular tertiary structure alignment-derived data.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_0888.name: Structure similarity score
data_0888.definition: A value representing molecular structure similarity, measured from structure alignment or some other type of structure comparison.

data_0889.name: Structural profile
data_0889.definition: Some type of structural (3D) profile or template (representing a structure or structure alignment).

data_0890.name: Structural (3D) profile alignment
data_0890.definition: A 3D profile-3D profile alignment (each profile representing structures or a structure alignment).

data_0891.name: Sequence-3D profile alignment
data_0891.definition: An alignment of a sequence to a 3D profile (representing structures or a structure alignment).

data_0892.name: Protein sequence-structure scoring matrix
data_0892.definition: Matrix of values used for scoring sequence-structure compatibility.

data_0893.name: Sequence-structure alignment
data_0893.definition: An alignment of molecular sequence to structure (from threading sequence(s) through 3D structure or representation of structure(s)).

data_0894.name: Amino acid annotation
data_0894.definition: An informative report about a specific amino acid.

data_0895.name: Peptide annotation
data_0895.definition: An informative report about a specific peptide.

data_0896.name: Protein report
data_0896.definition: An informative human-readable report about one or more specific protein molecules or protein structural domains, derived from analysis of primary (sequence or structural) data.

data_0897.name: Protein property
data_0897.definition:
A report of primarily non-positional data describing intrinsic physical, chemical or other properties of a protein molecule or model.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  Data may be based on analysis of nucleic acid sequence or structural data, for example reports on the surface properties (shape, hydropathy, electrostatic patches etc) of a protein structure, protein flexibility or motion, and protein architecture (spatial arrangement of secondary structure).

data_0900.name: Protein domain classification
data_0900.definition: Data concerning the classification of the sequences and/or structures of protein structural domain(s).

data_0901.name: Protein features report (domains)
data_0901.definition: structural domains or 3D folds in a protein or polypeptide chain.

data_0902.name: Protein architecture report
data_0902.definition: An informative report on architecture (spatial arrangement of secondary structure) of a protein structure.

data_0903.name: Protein folding report
data_0903.definition: A report on an analysis or model of protein folding properties, folding pathways, residues or sites that are key to protein folding, nucleation or stabilisation centers etc.

data_0904.name: Protein features (mutation)
data_0904.definition:
Data on the effect of (typically point) mutation on protein folding, stability, structure and function.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_0905.name: Protein interaction raw data
data_0905.definition:
Protein-protein interaction data from for example yeast two-hybrid analysis, protein microarrays, immunoaffinity chromatography followed by mass spectrometry, phage display etc.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_0906.name: Protein interaction data
data_0906.definition: Data concerning the interactions (predicted or known) within or between a protein, structural domain or part of a protein. This includes intra- and inter-residue contacts and distances, as well as interactions with other proteins and non-protein entities such as nucleic acid, metal atoms, water, ions etc.

data_0907.name: Protein family report
data_0907.definition: An informative report on a specific protein family or other classification or group of protein sequences or structures.

data_0909.name: Vmax
data_0909.definition: The maximum initial velocity or rate of a reaction. It is the limiting velocity as substrate concentrations get very large.

data_0910.name: Km
data_0910.definition: Km is the concentration (usually in Molar units) of substrate that leads to half-maximal velocity of an enzyme-catalysed reaction.

data_0911.name: Nucleotide base annotation
data_0911.definition: An informative report about a specific nucleotide base.

data_0912.name: Nucleic acid property
data_0912.definition:
A report of primarily non-positional data describing intrinsic physical, chemical or other properties of a nucleic acid molecule.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_0914.name: Codon usage data
data_0914.definition:
Data derived from analysis of codon usage (typically a codon usage table) of DNA sequences.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_0916.name: Gene report
data_0916.definition:
A report on predicted or actual gene structure, regions which make an RNA product and features such as promoters, coding regions, splice sites etc.
This includes any report on a particular locus or gene.  This might include the gene name, description, summary and so on. It can include details about the function of a gene, such as its encoded protein or a functional classification of the gene sequence along according to the encoded protein(s).
synonyms: Nucleic acid features (gene and transcript structure)

data_0917.name: Gene classification
data_0917.definition: A report on the classification of nucleic acid / gene sequences according to the functional classification of their gene products.

data_0918.name: DNA variation
data_0918.definition: stable, naturally occuring mutations in a nucleotide sequence including alleles, naturally occurring mutations such as single base nucleotide substitutions, deletions and insertions, RFLPs and other polymorphisms.

data_0919.name: Chromosome report
data_0919.definition:
A human-readable collection of information about a specific chromosome.
This includes basic information. e.g. chromosome number, length, karyotype features, chromosome sequence etc.

data_0920.name: Genotype/phenotype report
data_0920.definition: A human-readable collection of information about the set of genes (or allelic forms) present in an individual, organism or cell and associated with a specific physical characteristic, or a report concerning an organisms traits and phenotypes.

data_0923.name: PCR experiment report
data_0923.definition: PCR experiments, e.g. quantitative real-time PCR.

data_0924.name: Sequence trace
data_0924.definition:
Fluorescence trace data generated by an automated DNA sequencer, which can be interprted as a molecular sequence (reads), given associated sequencing metadata such as base-call quality scores.
This is the raw data produced by a DNA sequencing machine.

data_0925.name: Sequence assembly
data_0925.definition:
An assembly of fragments of a (typically genomic) DNA sequence.
Typically, an assembly is a collection of contigs (for example ESTs and genomic DNA fragments) that are ordered, aligned and merged. Annotation of the assembled sequence might be included.

data_0926.name: RH scores
data_0926.definition:
Radiation hybrid scores (RH) scores for one or more markers.
Radiation Hybrid (RH) scores are used in Radiation Hybrid mapping.

data_0927.name: Genetic linkage report
data_0927.definition:
A human-readable collection of information about the linkage of alleles.
This includes linkage disequilibrium; the non-random association of alleles or polymorphisms at two or more loci (not necessarily on the same chromosome).

data_0928.name: Gene expression profile
data_0928.definition: Data quantifying the level of expression of (typically) multiple genes, derived for example from microarray experiments.

data_0931.name: Microarray experiment report
data_0931.definition: microarray experiments including conditions, protocol, sample:data relationships etc.

data_0932.name: Oligonucleotide probe data
data_0932.definition: Data on oligonucleotide probes (typically for use with DNA microarrays).

data_0933.name: SAGE experimental data
data_0933.definition: Output from a serial analysis of gene expression (SAGE) experiment.

data_0936.name: Sequence tag profile (with gene assignment)
data_0936.definition: Tag to gene assignments (tag mapping) of SAGE, MPSS and SBS data. Typically this is the sequencing-based expression profile annotated with gene identifiers.

data_0938.name: Raw NMR data
data_0938.definition: Nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) raw data, typically for a protein.

data_0939.name: CD spectra
data_0939.definition: Protein secondary structure from protein coordinate or circular dichroism (CD) spectroscopic data.

data_0940.name: Volume map
data_0940.definition: Volume map data from electron microscopy.

data_0941.name: Electron microscopy model
data_0941.definition: Annotation on a structural 3D model (volume map) from electron microscopy.

data_0944.name: Peptide mass fingerprint
data_0944.definition:
A set of peptide masses (peptide mass fingerprint) from mass spectrometry.
A molecular weight standard fingerprint is standard protonated molecular masses e.g. from trypsin (modified porcine trypsin, Promega) and keratin peptides.

data_0945.name: Peptide identification
data_0945.definition: Protein or peptide identifications with evidence supporting the identifications, for example from comparing a peptide mass fingerprint (from mass spectrometry) to a sequence database, or  the set of typical spectra one obtains when running a protein through a mass spectrometer.

data_0946.name: Pathway or network annotation
data_0946.definition: An informative report about a specific biological pathway or network, typically including a map (diagram) of the pathway.

data_0947.name: Biological pathway map
data_0947.definition: A map (typically a diagram) of a biological pathway.

data_0948.name: Data resource definition
data_0948.definition: A definition of a data resource serving one or more types of data, including metadata and links to the resource or data proper.

data_0949.name: Workflow metadata
data_0949.definition: Basic information, annotation or documentation concerning a workflow (but not the workflow itself).

data_0950.name: Mathematical model
data_0950.definition: A biological model represented in mathematical terms.

data_0951.name: Statistical estimate score
data_0951.definition: A value representing estimated statistical significance of some observed data; typically sequence database hits.

data_0952.name: EMBOSS database resource definition
data_0952.definition: Resource definition for an EMBOSS database.

data_0953.name: Version information
data_0953.definition:
Information on a version of software or data, for example name, version number and release date.
Development status / maturity may be part of the version information, for example in case of tools, standards, or some data records.

data_0954.name: Database cross-mapping
data_0954.definition:
A mapping of the accession numbers (or other database identifier) of entries between (typically) two biological or biomedical databases.
The cross-mapping is typically a table where each row is an accession number and each column is a database being cross-referenced. The cells give the accession number or identifier of the corresponding entry in a database. If a cell in the table is not filled then no mapping could be found for the database. Additional information might be given on version, date etc.

data_0955.name: Data index
data_0955.definition: An index of data of biological relevance.

data_0956.name: Data index report
data_0956.definition: A human-readable collection of information concerning an analysis of an index of biological data.

data_0957.name: Database metadata
data_0957.definition: Basic information on bioinformatics database(s) or other data sources such as name, type, description, URL etc.

data_0958.name: Tool metadata
data_0958.definition: Basic information about one or more bioinformatics applications or packages, such as name, type, description, or other documentation.

data_0959.name: Job metadata
data_0959.definition: Textual metadata on a submitted or completed job.

data_0960.name: User metadata
data_0960.definition: Textual metadata on a software author or end-user, for example a person or other software.

data_0962.name: Small molecule report
data_0962.definition: A human-readable collection of information about a specific chemical compound.

data_0963.name: Cell line report
data_0963.definition: A human-readable collection of information about a particular strain of organism cell line including plants, virus, fungi and bacteria. The data typically includes strain number, organism type, growth conditions, source and so on.

data_0964.name: Scent annotation
data_0964.definition: An informative report about a specific scent.

data_0967.name: Ontology concept data
data_0967.definition: Data concerning or derived from a concept from a biological ontology.

data_0968.name: Keyword
data_0968.definition:
Keyword(s) or phrase(s) used (typically) for text-searching purposes.
Boolean operators (AND, OR and NOT) and wildcard characters may be allowed.

data_0970.name: Citation
data_0970.definition:
Bibliographic data that uniquely identifies a scientific article, book or other published material.
A bibliographic reference might include information such as authors, title, journal name, date and (possibly) a link to the abstract or full-text of the article if available.

data_0971.name: Article
data_0971.definition: A scientific text, typically a full text article from a scientific journal.

data_0972.name: Text mining report
data_0972.definition:
A human-readable collection of information resulting from text mining.
A text mining abstract will typically include an annotated a list of words or sentences extracted from one or more scientific articles.

data_0974.name: Entity identifier
data_0974.definition: An identifier of a biological entity or phenomenon.

data_0975.name: Data resource identifier
data_0975.definition: An identifier of a data resource.

data_0976.name: Identifier (by type of data)
data_0976.definition:
An identifier that identifies a particular type of data.
This concept exists only to assist EDAM maintenance and navigation in graphical browsers.  It does not add semantic information.  This branch provides an alternative organisation of the concepts nested under 'Accession' and 'Name'. All concepts under here are already included under 'Accession' or 'Name'.

data_0977.name: Tool identifier
data_0977.definition: An identifier of a bioinformatics tool, e.g. an application or web service.

data_0978.name: Discrete entity identifier
data_0978.definition: Name or other identifier of a discrete entity (any biological thing with a distinct, discrete physical existence).

data_0979.name: Entity feature identifier
data_0979.definition: Name or other identifier of an entity feature (a physical part or region of a discrete biological entity, or a feature that can be mapped to such a thing).

data_0980.name: Entity collection identifier
data_0980.definition: Name or other identifier of a collection of discrete biological entities.

data_0981.name: Phenomenon identifier
data_0981.definition: Name or other identifier of a physical, observable biological occurrence or event.

data_0982.name: Molecule identifier
data_0982.definition: Name or other identifier of a molecule.

data_0983.name: Atom ID
data_0983.definition: Identifier (e.g. character symbol) of a specific atom.

data_0985.name: Molecule type
data_0985.definition:
A label (text token) describing the type a molecule.
For example, 'Protein', 'DNA', 'RNA' etc.

data_0986.name: Chemical identifier
data_0986.definition: Unique identifier of a chemical compound.

data_0990.name: Compound name
data_0990.definition: Unique name of a chemical compound.

data_0991.name: Chemical registry number
data_0991.definition: Unique registry number of a chemical compound.

data_0992.name: Ligand identifier
data_0992.definition: Code word for a ligand, for example from a PDB file.

data_0995.name: Nucleotide identifier
data_0995.definition: Name or other identifier of a nucleotide.

data_0997.name: Chemical name (ChEBI)
data_0997.definition:
Unique name from Chemical Entities of Biological Interest (ChEBI) of a chemical compound.
This is the recommended chemical name for use for example in database annotation.

data_0998.name: Chemical name (IUPAC)
data_0998.definition: IUPAC recommended name of a chemical compound.

data_0999.name: Chemical name (INN)
data_0999.definition: International Non-proprietary Name (INN or 'generic name') of a chemical compound, assigned by the World Health Organisation (WHO).

data_1000.name: Chemical name (brand)
data_1000.definition: Brand name of a chemical compound.

data_1001.name: Chemical name (synonymous)
data_1001.definition: Synonymous name of a chemical compound.

data_1002.name: CAS number
data_1002.definition: CAS registry number of a chemical compound; a unique numerical identifier of chemicals in the scientific literature, as assigned by the Chemical Abstracts Service.

data_1003.name: Chemical registry number (Beilstein)
data_1003.definition: Beilstein registry number of a chemical compound.

data_1004.name: Chemical registry number (Gmelin)
data_1004.definition: Gmelin registry number of a chemical compound.

data_1005.name: HET group name
data_1005.definition: 3-letter code word for a ligand (HET group) from a PDB file, for example ATP.

data_1006.name: Amino acid name
data_1006.definition: String of one or more ASCII characters representing an amino acid.

data_1007.name: Nucleotide code
data_1007.definition: String of one or more ASCII characters representing a nucleotide.

data_1008.name: Polypeptide chain ID
data_1008.definition:
Identifier of a polypeptide chain from a protein.
This is typically a character (for the chain) appended to a PDB identifier, e.g. 1cukA

data_1010.name: Enzyme identifier
data_1010.definition: Name or other identifier of an enzyme or record from a database of enzymes.

data_1011.name: EC number
data_1011.definition: An Enzyme Commission (EC) number of an enzyme.

data_1014.name: Sequence position specification
data_1014.definition: A specification (partial or complete) of one or more positions or regions of a molecular sequence or map.

data_1015.name: Sequence feature ID
data_1015.definition: A unique identifier of molecular sequence feature, for example an ID of a feature that is unique within the scope of the GFF file.

data_1016.name: Sequence position
data_1016.definition: A position of one or more points (base or residue) in a sequence, or part of such a specification.

data_1017.name: Sequence range
data_1017.definition: Specification of range(s) of sequence positions.

data_1018.name: Nucleic acid feature identifier
data_1018.definition: Name or other identifier of an nucleic acid feature.

data_1019.name: Protein feature identifier
data_1019.definition: Name or other identifier of a protein feature.

data_1020.name: Sequence feature key
data_1020.definition:
The type of a sequence feature, typically a term or accession from the Sequence Ontology, for example an EMBL or Swiss-Prot sequence feature key.
A feature key indicates the biological nature of the feature or information about changes to or versions of the sequence.

data_1021.name: Sequence feature qualifier
data_1021.definition:
Typically one of the EMBL or Swiss-Prot feature qualifiers.
Feature qualifiers hold information about a feature beyond that provided by the feature key and location.

data_1022.name: Sequence feature label
data_1022.definition:
A name of a sequence feature, e.g. the name of a feature to be displayed to an end-user. Typically an EMBL or Swiss-Prot feature label.
A feature label identifies a feature of a sequence database entry. When used with the database name and the entry's primary accession number, it is a unique identifier of that feature.

data_1023.name: EMBOSS Uniform Feature Object
data_1023.definition: The name of a sequence feature-containing entity adhering to the standard feature naming scheme used by all EMBOSS applications.

data_1024.name: Codon name
data_1024.definition: String of one or more ASCII characters representing a codon.

data_1025.name: Gene identifier
data_1025.definition: An identifier of a gene, such as a name/symbol or a unique identifier of a gene in a database.

data_1026.name: Gene symbol
data_1026.definition: The short name of a gene; a single word that does not contain white space characters. It is typically derived from the gene name.

data_1027.name: Gene ID (NCBI)
data_1027.definition: An NCBI unique identifier of a gene.

data_1028.name: Gene identifier (NCBI RefSeq)
data_1028.definition: An NCBI RefSeq unique identifier of a gene.

data_1029.name: Gene identifier (NCBI UniGene)
data_1029.definition: An NCBI UniGene unique identifier of a gene.

data_1030.name: Gene identifier (Entrez)
data_1030.definition: An Entrez unique identifier of a gene.

data_1031.name: Gene ID (CGD)
data_1031.definition: Identifier of a gene or feature from the CGD database.

data_1032.name: Gene ID (DictyBase)
data_1032.definition: Identifier of a gene from DictyBase.

data_1033.name: Ensembl gene ID
data_1033.definition: Unique identifier for a gene (or other feature) from the Ensembl database.

data_1034.name: Gene ID (SGD)
data_1034.definition: Identifier of an entry from the SGD database.

data_1035.name: Gene ID (GeneDB)
data_1035.definition: Identifier of a gene from the GeneDB database.

data_1036.name: TIGR identifier
data_1036.definition: Identifier of an entry from the TIGR database.

data_1037.name: TAIR accession (gene)
data_1037.definition: Identifier of an gene from the TAIR database.

data_1038.name: Protein domain ID
data_1038.definition:
Identifier of a protein structural domain.
This is typically a character or string concatenated with a PDB identifier and a chain identifier.

data_1039.name: SCOP domain identifier
data_1039.definition: Identifier of a protein domain (or other node) from the SCOP database.

data_1040.name: CATH domain ID
data_1040.definition: Identifier of a protein domain from CATH.

data_1041.name: SCOP concise classification string (sccs)
data_1041.definition:
A SCOP concise classification string (sccs) is a compact representation of a SCOP domain classification.
An scss includes the class (alphabetical), fold, superfamily and family (all numerical) to which a given domain belongs.

data_1042.name: SCOP sunid
data_1042.definition:
Unique identifier (number) of an entry in the SCOP hierarchy, for example 33229.
A sunid uniquely identifies an entry in the SCOP hierarchy, including leaves (the SCOP domains) and higher level nodes including entries corresponding to the protein level.

data_1043.name: CATH node ID
data_1043.definition: A code number identifying a node from the CATH database.

data_1044.name: Kingdom name
data_1044.definition: The name of a biological kingdom (Bacteria, Archaea, or Eukaryotes).

data_1045.name: Species name
data_1045.definition: The name of a species (typically a taxonomic group) of organism.

data_1046.name: Strain name
data_1046.definition: The name of a strain of an organism variant, typically a plant, virus or bacterium.

data_1047.name: URI
data_1047.definition: A string of characters that name or otherwise identify a resource on the Internet.

data_1048.name: Database ID
data_1048.definition: An identifier of a biological or bioinformatics database.

data_1050.name: File name
data_1050.definition: The name (or part of a name) of a file (of any type).

data_1051.name: Ontology name
data_1051.definition: Name of an ontology of biological or bioinformatics concepts and relations.

data_1055.name: LSID
data_1055.definition:
A Life Science Identifier (LSID) - a unique identifier of some data.
LSIDs provide a standard way to locate and describe data. An LSID is represented as a Uniform Resource Name (URN) with the following format: URN:LSID:<Authority>:<Namespace>:<ObjectID>[:<Version>]

data_1056.name: Database name
data_1056.definition: The name of a biological or bioinformatics database.

data_1057.name: Sequence database name
data_1057.definition: The name of a molecular sequence database.

data_1058.name: Enumerated file name
data_1058.definition: The name of a file (of any type) with restricted possible values.

data_1059.name: File name extension
data_1059.definition:
The extension of a file name.
A file extension is the characters appearing after the final '.' in the file name.

data_1060.name: File base name
data_1060.definition:
The base name of a file.
A file base name is the file name stripped of its directory specification and extension.

data_1062.name: Database entry identifier
data_1062.definition:
An identifier of an entry from a database where the same type of identifier is used for objects (data) of different semantic type.
This concept is required for completeness. It should never have child concepts.

data_1063.name: Sequence identifier
data_1063.definition: An identifier of molecular sequence(s) or entries from a molecular sequence database.

data_1064.name: Sequence set ID
data_1064.definition: An identifier of a set of molecular sequence(s).

data_1065.name: Sequence signature identifier
data_1065.definition: Identifier of a sequence signature (motif or profile) for example from a database of sequence patterns.

data_1066.name: Sequence alignment ID
data_1066.definition: Identifier of a molecular sequence alignment, for example a record from an alignment database.

data_1067.name: Phylogenetic distance matrix identifier
data_1067.definition: Identifier of a phylogenetic distance matrix.

data_1068.name: Phylogenetic tree ID
data_1068.definition: Identifier of a phylogenetic tree for example from a phylogenetic tree database.

data_1069.name: Comparison matrix identifier
data_1069.definition: An identifier of a comparison matrix.

data_1070.name: Structure ID
data_1070.definition: A unique and persistent identifier of a molecular tertiary structure, typically an entry from a structure database.

data_1071.name: Structural (3D) profile ID
data_1071.definition: Identifier or name of a structural (3D) profile or template (representing a structure or structure alignment).

data_1072.name: Structure alignment ID
data_1072.definition: Identifier of an entry from a database of tertiary structure alignments.

data_1073.name: Amino acid index ID
data_1073.definition: Identifier of an index of amino acid physicochemical and biochemical property data.

data_1074.name: Protein interaction ID
data_1074.definition: Identifier of a report of protein interactions from a protein interaction database (typically).

data_1076.name: Codon usage table name
data_1076.definition: Unique name of a codon usage table.

data_1077.name: Transcription factor identifier
data_1077.definition: Identifier of a transcription factor (or a TF binding site).

data_1078.name: Experiment annotation ID
data_1078.definition: Identifier of an entry from a database of microarray data.

data_1079.name: Electron microscopy model ID
data_1079.definition: Identifier of an entry from a database of electron microscopy data.

data_1080.name: Gene expression report ID
data_1080.definition: Accession of a report of gene expression (e.g. a gene expression profile) from a database.

data_1081.name: Genotype and phenotype annotation ID
data_1081.definition: Identifier of an entry from a database of genotypes and phenotypes.

data_1082.name: Pathway or network identifier
data_1082.definition: Identifier of an entry from a database of biological pathways or networks.

data_1083.name: Workflow ID
data_1083.definition: Identifier of a biological or biomedical workflow, typically from a database of workflows.

data_1084.name: Data resource definition ID
data_1084.definition: Identifier of a data type definition from some provider.

data_1085.name: Biological model ID
data_1085.definition: Identifier of a mathematical model, typically an entry from a database.

data_1086.name: Compound identifier
data_1086.definition: Identifier of an entry from a database of chemicals.

data_1087.name: Ontology concept ID
data_1087.definition: A unique (typically numerical) identifier of a concept in an ontology of biological or bioinformatics concepts and relations.

data_1088.name: Article ID
data_1088.definition: Unique identifier of a scientific article.

data_1089.name: FlyBase ID
data_1089.definition: Identifier of an object from the FlyBase database.

data_1091.name: WormBase name
data_1091.definition: Name of an object from the WormBase database, usually a human-readable name.

data_1092.name: WormBase class
data_1092.definition:
Class of an object from the WormBase database.
A WormBase class describes the type of object such as 'sequence' or 'protein'.

data_1093.name: Sequence accession
data_1093.definition: A persistent, unique identifier of a molecular sequence database entry.

data_1094.name: Sequence type
data_1094.definition:
A label (text token) describing a type of molecular sequence.
Sequence type might reflect the molecule (protein, nucleic acid etc) or the sequence itself (gapped, ambiguous etc).

data_1095.name: EMBOSS Uniform Sequence Address
data_1095.definition: The name of a sequence-based entity adhering to the standard sequence naming scheme used by all EMBOSS applications.

data_1096.name: Sequence accession (protein)
data_1096.definition: Accession number of a protein sequence database entry.

data_1097.name: Sequence accession (nucleic acid)
data_1097.definition: Accession number of a nucleotide sequence database entry.

data_1098.name: RefSeq accession
data_1098.definition: Accession number of a RefSeq database entry.

data_1099.name: UniProt accession (extended)
data_1099.definition: Accession number of a UniProt (protein sequence) database entry. May contain version or isoform number.

data_1100.name: PIR identifier
data_1100.definition: An identifier of PIR sequence database entry.

data_1101.name: TREMBL accession
data_1101.definition: Identifier of a TREMBL sequence database entry.

data_1102.name: Gramene primary identifier
data_1102.definition: Primary identifier of a Gramene database entry.

data_1103.name: EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ ID
data_1103.definition: Identifier of a (nucleic acid) entry from the EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ databases.

data_1104.name: Sequence cluster ID (UniGene)
data_1104.definition: A unique identifier of an entry (gene cluster) from the NCBI UniGene database.

data_1105.name: dbEST accession
data_1105.definition: Identifier of a dbEST database entry.

data_1106.name: dbSNP ID
data_1106.definition: Identifier of a dbSNP database entry.

data_1110.name: EMBOSS sequence type
data_1110.definition:
The EMBOSS type of a molecular sequence.
See the EMBOSS documentation (http://emboss.sourceforge.net/) for a definition of what this includes.

data_1111.name: EMBOSS listfile
data_1111.definition: List of EMBOSS Uniform Sequence Addresses (EMBOSS listfile).

data_1112.name: Sequence cluster ID
data_1112.definition: An identifier of a cluster of molecular sequence(s).

data_1113.name: Sequence cluster ID (COG)
data_1113.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the COG database.

data_1114.name: Sequence motif identifier
data_1114.definition: Identifier of a sequence motif, for example an entry from a motif database.

data_1115.name: Sequence profile ID
data_1115.definition:
Identifier of a sequence profile.
A sequence profile typically represents a sequence alignment.

data_1116.name: ELM ID
data_1116.definition: Identifier of an entry from the ELMdb database of protein functional sites.

data_1117.name: Prosite accession number
data_1117.definition: Accession number of an entry from the Prosite database.

data_1118.name: HMMER hidden Markov model ID
data_1118.definition: Unique identifier or name of a HMMER hidden Markov model.

data_1119.name: JASPAR profile ID
data_1119.definition: Unique identifier or name of a profile from the JASPAR database.

data_1120.name: Sequence alignment type
data_1120.definition:
A label (text token) describing the type of a sequence alignment.
Possible values include for example the EMBOSS alignment types, BLAST alignment types and so on.

data_1121.name: BLAST sequence alignment type
data_1121.definition: The type of a BLAST sequence alignment.

data_1122.name: Phylogenetic tree type
data_1122.definition:
A label (text token) describing the type of a phylogenetic tree.
For example 'nj', 'upgmp' etc.

data_1123.name: TreeBASE study accession number
data_1123.definition: Accession number of an entry from the TreeBASE database.

data_1124.name: TreeFam accession number
data_1124.definition: Accession number of an entry from the TreeFam database.

data_1125.name: Comparison matrix type
data_1125.definition:
A label (text token) describing the type of a comparison matrix.
For example 'blosum', 'pam', 'gonnet', 'id' etc. Comparison matrix type may be required where a series of matrices of a certain type are used.

data_1126.name: Comparison matrix name
data_1126.definition:
Unique name or identifier of a comparison matrix.
See for example http://www.ebi.ac.uk/Tools/webservices/help/matrix.

data_1127.name: PDB ID
data_1127.definition:
An identifier of an entry from the PDB database.
A PDB identification code which consists of 4 characters, the first of which is a digit in the range 0 - 9; the remaining 3 are alpha-numeric, and letters are upper case only. (source: https://cdn.rcsb.org/wwpdb/docs/documentation/file-format/PDB_format_1996.pdf)

data_1128.name: AAindex ID
data_1128.definition: Identifier of an entry from the AAindex database.

data_1129.name: BIND accession number
data_1129.definition: Accession number of an entry from the BIND database.

data_1130.name: IntAct accession number
data_1130.definition: Accession number of an entry from the IntAct database.

data_1132.name: InterPro entry name
data_1132.definition: Name of an InterPro entry, usually indicating the type of protein matches for that entry.

data_1133.name: InterPro accession
data_1133.definition:
Primary accession number of an InterPro entry.
Every InterPro entry has a unique accession number to provide a persistent citation of database records.

data_1134.name: InterPro secondary accession
data_1134.definition: Secondary accession number of an InterPro entry.

data_1135.name: Gene3D ID
data_1135.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the Gene3D database.

data_1136.name: PIRSF ID
data_1136.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the PIRSF database.

data_1137.name: PRINTS code
data_1137.definition: The unique identifier of an entry in the PRINTS database.

data_1138.name: Pfam accession number
data_1138.definition: Accession number of a Pfam entry.

data_1139.name: SMART accession number
data_1139.definition: Accession number of an entry from the SMART database.

data_1140.name: Superfamily hidden Markov model number
data_1140.definition: Unique identifier (number) of a hidden Markov model from the Superfamily database.

data_1141.name: TIGRFam ID
data_1141.definition: Accession number of an entry (family) from the TIGRFam database.

data_1142.name: ProDom accession number
data_1142.definition:
A ProDom domain family accession number.
ProDom is a protein domain family database.

data_1143.name: TRANSFAC accession number
data_1143.definition: Identifier of an entry from the TRANSFAC database.

data_1144.name: ArrayExpress accession number
data_1144.definition: Accession number of an entry from the ArrayExpress database.

data_1146.name: EMDB ID
data_1146.definition: Identifier of an entry from the EMDB electron microscopy database.

data_1147.name: GEO accession number
data_1147.definition: Accession number of an entry from the GEO database.

data_1148.name: GermOnline ID
data_1148.definition: Identifier of an entry from the GermOnline database.

data_1149.name: EMAGE ID
data_1149.definition: Identifier of an entry from the EMAGE database.

data_1150.name: Disease ID
data_1150.definition: Accession number of an entry from a database of disease.

data_1151.name: HGVbase ID
data_1151.definition: Identifier of an entry from the HGVbase database.

data_1152.name: HIVDB identifier
data_1152.definition: Identifier of an entry from the HIVDB database.

data_1153.name: OMIM ID
data_1153.definition: Identifier of an entry from the OMIM database.

data_1154.name: KEGG object identifier
data_1154.definition: Unique identifier of an object from one of the KEGG databases (excluding the GENES division).

data_1155.name: Pathway ID (reactome)
data_1155.definition: Identifier of an entry from the Reactome database.

data_1156.name: Pathway ID (aMAZE)
data_1156.definition: Identifier of an entry from the aMAZE database.

data_1157.name: Pathway ID (BioCyc)
data_1157.definition: Identifier of an pathway from the BioCyc biological pathways database.

data_1158.name: Pathway ID (INOH)
data_1158.definition: Identifier of an entry from the INOH database.

data_1159.name: Pathway ID (PATIKA)
data_1159.definition: Identifier of an entry from the PATIKA database.

data_1160.name: Pathway ID (CPDB)
data_1160.definition:
Identifier of an entry from the CPDB (ConsensusPathDB) biological pathways database, which is an identifier from an external database integrated into CPDB.
This concept refers to identifiers used by the databases collated in CPDB; CPDB identifiers are not independently defined.

data_1161.name: Pathway ID (Panther)
data_1161.definition: Identifier of a biological pathway from the Panther Pathways database.

data_1162.name: MIRIAM identifier
data_1162.definition:
Unique identifier of a MIRIAM data resource.
This is the identifier used internally by MIRIAM for a data type.

data_1163.name: MIRIAM data type name
data_1163.definition: The name of a data type from the MIRIAM database.

data_1164.name: MIRIAM URI
data_1164.definition:
The URI (URL or URN) of a data entity from the MIRIAM database.
A MIRIAM URI consists of the URI of the MIRIAM data type (PubMed, UniProt etc) followed by the identifier of an element of that data type, for example PMID for a publication or an accession number for a GO term.

data_1165.name: MIRIAM data type primary name
data_1165.definition:
The primary name of a data type from the MIRIAM database.
The primary name of a MIRIAM data type is taken from a controlled vocabulary.

data_1166.name: MIRIAM data type synonymous name
data_1166.definition:
A synonymous name of a data type from the MIRIAM database.
A synonymous name for a MIRIAM data type taken from a controlled vocabulary.

data_1167.name: Taverna workflow ID
data_1167.definition: Unique identifier of a Taverna workflow.

data_1171.name: BioModel ID
data_1171.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the BioModel database.

data_1172.name: PubChem CID
data_1172.definition: Chemical structure specified in PubChem Compound Identification (CID), a non-zero integer identifier for a unique chemical structure.

data_1173.name: ChemSpider ID
data_1173.definition: Identifier of an entry from the ChemSpider database.

data_1174.name: ChEBI ID
data_1174.definition: Identifier of an entry from the ChEBI database.

data_1175.name: BioPax concept ID
data_1175.definition: An identifier of a concept from the BioPax ontology.

data_1176.name: GO concept ID
data_1176.definition: An identifier of a concept from The Gene Ontology.

data_1177.name: MeSH concept ID
data_1177.definition: An identifier of a concept from the MeSH vocabulary.

data_1178.name: HGNC concept ID
data_1178.definition: An identifier of a concept from the HGNC controlled vocabulary.

data_1179.name: NCBI taxonomy ID
data_1179.definition: A stable unique identifier for each taxon (for a species, a family, an order, or any other group in the NCBI taxonomy database.

data_1180.name: Plant Ontology concept ID
data_1180.definition: An identifier of a concept from the Plant Ontology (PO).

data_1181.name: UMLS concept ID
data_1181.definition: An identifier of a concept from the UMLS vocabulary.

data_1182.name: FMA concept ID
data_1182.definition:
An identifier of a concept from Foundational Model of Anatomy.
Classifies anatomical entities according to their shared characteristics (genus) and distinguishing characteristics (differentia). Specifies the part-whole and spatial relationships of the entities, morphological transformation of the entities during prenatal development and the postnatal life cycle and principles, rules and definitions according to which classes and relationships in the other three components of FMA are represented.

data_1183.name: EMAP concept ID
data_1183.definition: An identifier of a concept from the EMAP mouse ontology.

data_1184.name: ChEBI concept ID
data_1184.definition: An identifier of a concept from the ChEBI ontology.

data_1185.name: MGED concept ID
data_1185.definition: An identifier of a concept from the MGED ontology.

data_1186.name: myGrid concept ID
data_1186.definition:
An identifier of a concept from the myGrid ontology.
The ontology is provided as two components, the service ontology and the domain ontology. The domain ontology acts provides concepts for core bioinformatics data types and their relations. The service ontology describes the physical and operational features of web services.

data_1187.name: PubMed ID
data_1187.definition: PubMed unique identifier of an article.

data_1188.name: DOI
data_1188.definition: Digital Object Identifier (DOI) of a published article.

data_1189.name: Medline UI
data_1189.definition:
Medline UI (unique identifier) of an article.
The use of Medline UI has been replaced by the PubMed unique identifier.

data_1190.name: Tool name
data_1190.definition: The name of a computer package, application, method or function.

data_1191.name: Tool name (signature)
data_1191.definition:
The unique name of a signature (sequence classifier) method.
Signature methods from http://www.ebi.ac.uk/Tools/InterProScan/help.html#results include BlastProDom, FPrintScan, HMMPIR, HMMPfam, HMMSmart, HMMTigr, ProfileScan, ScanRegExp, SuperFamily and HAMAP.

data_1192.name: Tool name (BLAST)
data_1192.definition:
The name of a BLAST tool.
This include 'blastn', 'blastp', 'blastx', 'tblastn' and 'tblastx'.

data_1193.name: Tool name (FASTA)
data_1193.definition:
The name of a FASTA tool.
This includes 'fasta3', 'fastx3', 'fasty3', 'fastf3', 'fasts3' and 'ssearch'.

data_1194.name: Tool name (EMBOSS)
data_1194.definition: The name of an EMBOSS application.

data_1195.name: Tool name (EMBASSY package)
data_1195.definition: The name of an EMBASSY package.

data_1233.name: Sequence set (protein)
data_1233.definition: Any collection of multiple protein sequences and associated metadata that do not (typically) correspond to common sequence database records or database entries.

data_1234.name: Sequence set (nucleic acid)
data_1234.definition: Any collection of multiple nucleotide sequences and associated metadata that do not (typically) correspond to common sequence database records or database entries.

data_1235.name: Sequence cluster
data_1235.definition:
A set of sequences that have been clustered or otherwise classified as belonging to a group including (typically) sequence cluster information.
The cluster might include sequences identifiers, short descriptions, alignment and summary information.

data_1236.name: Psiblast checkpoint file
data_1236.definition:
A file of intermediate results from a PSIBLAST search that is used for priming the search in the next PSIBLAST iteration.
A Psiblast checkpoint file uses ASN.1 Binary Format and usually has the extension '.asn'.

data_1237.name: HMMER synthetic sequences set
data_1237.definition: Sequences generated by HMMER package in FASTA-style format.

data_1238.name: Proteolytic digest
data_1238.definition: A protein sequence cleaved into peptide fragments (by enzymatic or chemical cleavage) with fragment masses.

data_1239.name: Restriction digest
data_1239.definition: Restriction digest fragments from digesting a nucleotide sequence with restriction sites using a restriction endonuclease.

data_1240.name: PCR primers
data_1240.definition: Oligonucleotide primer(s) for PCR and DNA amplification, for example a minimal primer set.

data_1241.name: vectorstrip cloning vector definition file
data_1241.definition: File of sequence vectors used by EMBOSS vectorstrip application, or any file in same format.

data_1242.name: Primer3 internal oligo mishybridizing library
data_1242.definition: A library of nucleotide sequences to avoid during hybridisation events. Hybridisation of the internal oligo to sequences in this library is avoided, rather than priming from them. The file is in a restricted FASTA format.

data_1243.name: Primer3 mispriming library file
data_1243.definition: A nucleotide sequence library of sequences to avoid during amplification (for example repetitive sequences, or possibly the sequences of genes in a gene family that should not be amplified. The file must is in a restricted FASTA format.

data_1244.name: primersearch primer pairs sequence record
data_1244.definition: File of one or more pairs of primer sequences, as used by EMBOSS primersearch application.

data_1245.name: Sequence cluster (protein)
data_1245.definition:
A cluster of protein sequences.
The sequences are typically related, for example a family of sequences.

data_1246.name: Sequence cluster (nucleic acid)
data_1246.definition:
A cluster of nucleotide sequences.
The sequences are typically related, for example a family of sequences.

data_1249.name: Sequence length
data_1249.definition: The size (length) of a sequence, subsequence or region in a sequence, or range(s) of lengths.

data_1250.name: Word size
data_1250.definition:
Size of a sequence word.
Word size is used for example in word-based sequence database search methods.

data_1251.name: Window size
data_1251.definition:
Size of a sequence window.
A window is a region of fixed size but not fixed position over a molecular sequence. It is typically moved (computationally) over a sequence during scoring.

data_1252.name: Sequence length range
data_1252.definition: Specification of range(s) of length of sequences.

data_1253.name: Sequence information report
data_1253.definition: Report on basic information about a molecular sequence such as name, accession number, type (nucleic or protein), length, description etc.

data_1254.name: Sequence property
data_1254.definition: An informative report about non-positional sequence features, typically a report on general molecular sequence properties derived from sequence analysis.

data_1255.name: Sequence features
data_1255.definition:
Annotation of positional features of molecular sequence(s), i.e. that can be mapped to position(s) in the sequence.
This includes annotation of positional sequence features, organised into a standard feature table, or any other report of sequence features.  General feature reports are a source of sequence feature table information although internal conversion would be required.

data_1256.name: Sequence features (comparative)
data_1256.definition:
Comparative data on sequence features such as statistics, intersections (and data on intersections), differences etc.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_1257.name: Sequence property (protein)
data_1257.definition: A report of general sequence properties derived from protein sequence data.

data_1258.name: Sequence property (nucleic acid)
data_1258.definition: A report of general sequence properties derived from nucleotide sequence data.

data_1259.name: Sequence complexity report
data_1259.definition: A report on sequence complexity, for example low-complexity or repeat regions in sequences.

data_1260.name: Sequence ambiguity report
data_1260.definition: A report on ambiguity in molecular sequence(s).

data_1261.name: Sequence composition report
data_1261.definition: A report (typically a table) on character or word composition / frequency of a molecular sequence(s).

data_1262.name: Peptide molecular weight hits
data_1262.definition: A report on peptide fragments of certain molecular weight(s) in one or more protein sequences.

data_1263.name: Base position variability plot
data_1263.definition: A plot of third base position variability in a nucleotide sequence.

data_1264.name: Sequence composition table
data_1264.definition: A table of character or word composition / frequency of a molecular sequence.

data_1265.name: Base frequencies table
data_1265.definition: A table of base frequencies of a nucleotide sequence.

data_1266.name: Base word frequencies table
data_1266.definition: A table of word composition of a nucleotide sequence.

data_1267.name: Amino acid frequencies table
data_1267.definition: A table of amino acid frequencies of a protein sequence.

data_1268.name: Amino acid word frequencies table
data_1268.definition: A table of amino acid word composition of a protein sequence.

data_1269.name: DAS sequence feature annotation
data_1269.definition: Annotation of a molecular sequence in DAS format.

data_1270.name: Feature table
data_1270.definition: Annotation of positional sequence features, organised into a standard feature table.

data_1274.name: Map
data_1274.definition: A map of (typically one) DNA sequence annotated with positional or non-positional features.

data_1276.name: Nucleic acid features
data_1276.definition:
An informative report on intrinsic positional features of a nucleotide sequence, formatted to be machine-readable.
This includes nucleotide sequence feature annotation in any known sequence feature table format and any other report of nucleic acid features.

data_1277.name: Protein features
data_1277.definition:
An informative report on intrinsic positional features of a protein sequence.
This includes protein sequence feature annotation in any known sequence feature table format and any other report of protein features.

data_1278.name: Genetic map
data_1278.definition:
A map showing the relative positions of genetic markers in a nucleic acid sequence, based on estimation of non-physical distance such as recombination frequencies.
A genetic (linkage) map indicates the proximity of two genes on a chromosome, whether two genes are linked and the frequency they are transmitted together to an offspring. They are limited to genetic markers of traits observable only in whole organisms.

data_1279.name: Sequence map
data_1279.definition:
A map of genetic markers in a contiguous, assembled genomic sequence, with the sizes and separation of markers measured in base pairs.
A sequence map typically includes annotation on significant subsequences such as contigs, haplotypes and genes. The contigs shown will (typically) be a set of small overlapping clones representing a complete chromosomal segment.

data_1280.name: Physical map
data_1280.definition:
A map of DNA (linear or circular) annotated with physical features or landmarks such as restriction sites, cloned DNA fragments, genes or genetic markers, along with the physical distances between them.
Distance in a physical map is measured in base pairs. A physical map might be ordered relative to a reference map (typically a genetic map) in the process of genome sequencing.

data_1281.name: Sequence signature map
data_1281.definition: Image of a sequence with matches to signatures, motifs or profiles.

data_1283.name: Cytogenetic map
data_1283.definition:
A map showing banding patterns derived from direct observation of a stained chromosome.
This is the lowest-resolution physical map and can provide only rough estimates of physical (base pair) distances.  Like a genetic map, they are limited to genetic markers of traits observable only in whole organisms.

data_1284.name: DNA transduction map
data_1284.definition: A gene map showing distances between loci based on relative cotransduction frequencies.

data_1285.name: Gene map
data_1285.definition: Sequence map of a single gene annotated with genetic features such as introns, exons, untranslated regions, polyA signals, promoters, enhancers and (possibly) mutations defining alleles of a gene.

data_1286.name: Plasmid map
data_1286.definition: Sequence map of a plasmid (circular DNA).

data_1288.name: Genome map
data_1288.definition: Sequence map of a whole genome.

data_1289.name: Restriction map
data_1289.definition: Image of the restriction enzyme cleavage sites (restriction sites) in a nucleic acid sequence.

data_1290.name: InterPro compact match image
data_1290.definition:
Image showing matches between protein sequence(s) and InterPro Entries.
The sequence(s) might be screened against InterPro, or be the sequences from the InterPro entry itself. Each protein is represented as a scaled horizontal line with colored bars indicating the position of the matches.

data_1291.name: InterPro detailed match image
data_1291.definition:
Image showing detailed information on matches between protein sequence(s) and InterPro Entries.
The sequence(s) might be screened against InterPro, or be the sequences from the InterPro entry itself.

data_1292.name: InterPro architecture image
data_1292.definition:
Image showing the architecture of InterPro domains in a protein sequence.
The sequence(s) might be screened against InterPro, or be the sequences from the InterPro entry itself. Domain architecture is shown as a series of non-overlapping domains in the protein.

data_1293.name: SMART protein schematic
data_1293.definition: SMART protein schematic in PNG format.

data_1294.name: GlobPlot domain image
data_1294.definition: Images based on GlobPlot prediction of intrinsic disordered regions and globular domains in protein sequences.

data_1298.name: Sequence motif matches
data_1298.definition: Report on the location of matches to profiles, motifs (conserved or functional patterns) or other signatures in one or more sequences.

data_1299.name: Sequence features (repeats)
data_1299.definition:
Location of short repetitive subsequences (repeat sequences) in (typically nucleotide) sequences.
The report might include derived data map such as classification, annotation, organisation, periodicity etc.

data_1300.name: Gene and transcript structure (report)
data_1300.definition: A report on predicted or actual gene structure, regions which make an RNA product and features such as promoters, coding regions, splice sites etc.

data_1301.name: Mobile genetic elements
data_1301.definition: regions of a nucleic acid sequence containing mobile genetic elements.

data_1303.name: Nucleic acid features (quadruplexes)
data_1303.definition: A report on quadruplex-forming motifs in a nucleotide sequence.

data_1306.name: Nucleosome exclusion sequences
data_1306.definition: Report on nucleosome formation potential or exclusion sequence(s).

data_1309.name: Gene features (exonic splicing enhancer)
data_1309.definition: A report on exonic splicing enhancers (ESE) in an exon.

data_1310.name: Nucleic acid features (microRNA)
data_1310.definition: A report on microRNA sequence (miRNA) or precursor, microRNA targets, miRNA binding sites in an RNA sequence etc.

data_1313.name: Coding region
data_1313.definition: protein-coding regions including coding sequences (CDS), exons, translation initiation sites and open reading frames.

data_1314.name: Gene features (SECIS element)
data_1314.definition: A report on selenocysteine insertion sequence (SECIS) element in a DNA sequence.

data_1315.name: Transcription factor binding sites
data_1315.definition: transcription factor binding sites (TFBS) in a DNA sequence.

data_1321.name: Protein features (sites)
data_1321.definition:
A report on predicted or known key residue positions (sites) in a protein sequence, such as binding or functional sites.
Use this concept for collections of specific sites which are not necessarily contiguous, rather than contiguous stretches of amino acids.

data_1322.name: Protein features report (signal peptides)
data_1322.definition: signal peptides or signal peptide cleavage sites in protein sequences.

data_1323.name: Protein features report (cleavage sites)
data_1323.definition: cleavage sites (for a proteolytic enzyme or agent) in a protein sequence.

data_1324.name: Protein features (post-translation modifications)
data_1324.definition: post-translation modifications in a protein sequence, typically describing the specific sites involved.

data_1325.name: Protein features report (active sites)
data_1325.definition: catalytic residues (active site) of an enzyme.

data_1326.name: Protein features report (binding sites)
data_1326.definition: ligand-binding (non-catalytic) residues of a protein, such as sites that bind metal, prosthetic groups or lipids.

data_1327.name: Protein features (epitopes)
data_1327.definition:
A report on antigenic determinant sites (epitopes) in proteins, from sequence and / or structural data.
Epitope mapping is commonly done during vaccine design.

data_1328.name: Protein features report (nucleic acid binding sites)
data_1328.definition: RNA and DNA-binding proteins and binding sites in protein sequences.

data_1329.name: MHC Class I epitopes report
data_1329.definition: A report on epitopes that bind to MHC class I molecules.

data_1330.name: MHC Class II epitopes report
data_1330.definition: A report on predicted epitopes that bind to MHC class II molecules.

data_1331.name: Protein features (PEST sites)
data_1331.definition:
A report or plot of PEST sites in a protein sequence.
'PEST' motifs target proteins for proteolytic degradation and reduce the half-lives of proteins dramatically.

data_1338.name: Sequence database hits scores list
data_1338.definition: Scores from a sequence database search (for example a BLAST search).

data_1339.name: Sequence database hits alignments list
data_1339.definition: Alignments from a sequence database search (for example a BLAST search).

data_1340.name: Sequence database hits evaluation data
data_1340.definition: A report on the evaluation of the significance of sequence similarity scores from a sequence database search (for example a BLAST search).

data_1344.name: MEME motif alphabet
data_1344.definition: Alphabet for the motifs (patterns) that MEME will search for.

data_1346.name: MEME motifs directive file
data_1346.definition: File of directives for ordering and spacing of MEME motifs.

data_1347.name: Dirichlet distribution
data_1347.definition: Dirichlet distribution used by hidden Markov model analysis programs.

data_1348.name: HMM emission and transition counts
data_1348.definition: Emission and transition counts of a hidden Markov model, generated once HMM has been determined, for example after residues/gaps have been assigned to match, delete and insert states.

data_1353.name: Sequence motif
data_1353.definition: Any specific or conserved pattern (typically expressed as a regular expression) in a molecular sequence.

data_1354.name: Sequence profile
data_1354.definition: Some type of statistical model representing a (typically multiple) sequence alignment.

data_1355.name: Protein signature
data_1355.definition: An informative report about a specific or conserved protein sequence pattern.

data_1358.name: Prosite nucleotide pattern
data_1358.definition: A nucleotide regular expression pattern from the Prosite database.

data_1359.name: Prosite protein pattern
data_1359.definition: A protein regular expression pattern from the Prosite database.

data_1361.name: Position frequency matrix
data_1361.definition: A profile (typically representing a sequence alignment) that is a simple matrix of nucleotide (or amino acid) counts per position.

data_1362.name: Position weight matrix
data_1362.definition:
A profile (typically representing a sequence alignment) that is weighted matrix of nucleotide (or amino acid) counts per position.
Contributions of individual sequences to the matrix might be uneven (weighted).

data_1363.name: Information content matrix
data_1363.definition: A profile (typically representing a sequence alignment) derived from a matrix of nucleotide (or amino acid) counts per position that reflects information content at each position.

data_1364.name: Hidden Markov model
data_1364.definition: A statistical Markov model of a system which is assumed to be a Markov process with unobserved (hidden) states.  For example, a hidden Markov model representation of a set or alignment of sequences.

data_1365.name: Fingerprint
data_1365.definition: One or more fingerprints (sequence classifiers) as used in the PRINTS database.

data_1368.name: Domainatrix signature
data_1368.definition: A protein signature of the type used in the EMBASSY Signature package.

data_1371.name: HMMER NULL hidden Markov model
data_1371.definition: NULL hidden Markov model representation used by the HMMER package.

data_1372.name: Protein family signature
data_1372.definition:
A protein family signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
Protein family signatures cover all domains in the matching proteins and span >80% of the protein length and with no adjacent protein domain signatures or protein region signatures.

data_1373.name: Protein domain signature
data_1373.definition:
A protein domain signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
Protein domain signatures identify structural or functional domains or other units with defined boundaries.

data_1374.name: Protein region signature
data_1374.definition:
A protein region signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
A protein region signature defines a region which cannot be described as a protein family or domain signature.

data_1375.name: Protein repeat signature
data_1375.definition:
A protein repeat signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
A protein repeat signature is a repeated protein motif, that is not in single copy expected to independently fold into a globular domain.

data_1376.name: Protein site signature
data_1376.definition:
A protein site signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
A protein site signature is a classifier for a specific site in a protein.

data_1377.name: Protein conserved site signature
data_1377.definition:
A protein conserved site signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
A protein conserved site signature is any short sequence pattern that may contain one or more unique residues and is cannot be described as a active site, binding site or post-translational modification.

data_1378.name: Protein active site signature
data_1378.definition:
A protein active site signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
A protein active site signature corresponds to an enzyme catalytic pocket. An active site typically includes non-contiguous residues, therefore multiple signatures may be required to describe an active site. ; residues involved in enzymatic reactions for which mutational data is typically available.

data_1379.name: Protein binding site signature
data_1379.definition:
A protein binding site signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
A protein binding site signature corresponds to a site that reversibly binds chemical compounds, which are not themselves substrates of the enzymatic reaction. This includes enzyme cofactors and residues involved in electron transport or protein structure modification.

data_1380.name: Protein post-translational modification signature
data_1380.definition:
A protein post-translational modification signature (sequence classifier) from the InterPro database.
A protein post-translational modification signature corresponds to sites that undergo modification of the primary structure, typically to activate or de-activate a function. For example, methylation, sumoylation, glycosylation etc. The modification might be permanent or reversible.

data_1381.name: Pair sequence alignment
data_1381.definition: Alignment of exactly two molecular sequences.

data_1382.name: Sequence alignment (multiple)
data_1382.definition: Alignment of more than two molecular sequences.

data_1385.name: Hybrid sequence alignment
data_1385.definition:
Alignment of multiple molecular sequences of different types.
Hybrid sequence alignments include for example genomic DNA to EST, cDNA or mRNA.

data_1386.name: Sequence alignment (nucleic acid pair)
data_1386.definition: Alignment of exactly two nucleotide sequences.

data_1387.name: Sequence alignment (protein pair)
data_1387.definition: Alignment of exactly two protein sequences.

data_1388.name: Hybrid sequence alignment (pair)
data_1388.definition: Alignment of exactly two molecular sequences of different types.

data_1389.name: Multiple nucleotide sequence alignment
data_1389.definition: Alignment of more than two nucleotide sequences.

data_1390.name: Multiple protein sequence alignment
data_1390.definition: Alignment of more than two protein sequences.

data_1394.name: Alignment score or penalty
data_1394.definition: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for opening or extending a gap in an alignment.

data_1395.name: Score end gaps control
data_1395.definition: Whether end gaps are scored or not.

data_1396.name: Aligned sequence order
data_1396.definition: Controls the order of sequences in an output sequence alignment.

data_1397.name: Gap opening penalty
data_1397.definition: A penalty for opening a gap in an alignment.

data_1398.name: Gap extension penalty
data_1398.definition: A penalty for extending a gap in an alignment.

data_1399.name: Gap separation penalty
data_1399.definition: A penalty for gaps that are close together in an alignment.

data_1400.name: Terminal gap penalty
data_1400.definition: A penalty for gaps at the termini of an alignment, either from the N/C terminal of protein or 5'/3' terminal of nucleotide sequences.

data_1401.name: Match reward score
data_1401.definition: The score for a 'match' used in various sequence database search applications with simple scoring schemes.

data_1402.name: Mismatch penalty score
data_1402.definition: The score (penalty) for a 'mismatch' used in various alignment and sequence database search applications with simple scoring schemes.

data_1403.name: Drop off score
data_1403.definition: This is the threshold drop in score at which extension of word alignment is halted.

data_1404.name: Gap opening penalty (integer)
data_1404.definition: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for opening a gap in an alignment.

data_1405.name: Gap opening penalty (float)
data_1405.definition: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for opening a gap in an alignment.

data_1406.name: Gap extension penalty (integer)
data_1406.definition: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for extending a gap in an alignment.

data_1407.name: Gap extension penalty (float)
data_1407.definition: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for extending a gap in an alignment.

data_1408.name: Gap separation penalty (integer)
data_1408.definition: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for gaps that are close together in an alignment.

data_1409.name: Gap separation penalty (float)
