data_1409.definition: A simple floating point number defining the penalty for gaps that are close together in an alignment.

data_1410.name: Terminal gap opening penalty
data_1410.definition: A number defining the penalty for opening gaps at the termini of an alignment, either from the N/C terminal of protein or 5'/3' terminal of nucleotide sequences.

data_1411.name: Terminal gap extension penalty
data_1411.definition: A number defining the penalty for extending gaps at the termini of an alignment, either from the N/C terminal of protein or 5'/3' terminal of nucleotide sequences.

data_1412.name: Sequence identity
data_1412.definition: Sequence identity is the number (%) of matches (identical characters) in positions from an alignment of two molecular sequences.

data_1413.name: Sequence similarity
data_1413.definition:
Sequence similarity is the similarity (expressed as a percentage) of two molecular sequences calculated from their alignment, a scoring matrix for scoring characters substitutions and penalties for gap insertion and extension.
Data Type is float probably.

data_1414.name: Sequence alignment metadata (quality report)
data_1414.definition: Data on molecular sequence alignment quality (estimated accuracy).

data_1415.name: Sequence alignment report (site conservation)
data_1415.definition:
Data on character conservation in a molecular sequence alignment.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation. Use this concept for calculated substitution rates, relative site variability, data on sites with biased properties, highly conserved or very poorly conserved sites, regions, blocks etc.

data_1416.name: Sequence alignment report (site correlation)
data_1416.definition: Data on correlations between sites in a molecular sequence alignment, typically to identify possible covarying positions and predict contacts or structural constraints in protein structures.

data_1417.name: Sequence-profile alignment (Domainatrix signature)
data_1417.definition: Alignment of molecular sequences to a Domainatrix signature (representing a sequence alignment).

data_1418.name: Sequence-profile alignment (HMM)
data_1418.definition: Alignment of molecular sequence(s) to a hidden Markov model(s).

data_1420.name: Sequence-profile alignment (fingerprint)
data_1420.definition: Alignment of molecular sequences to a protein fingerprint from the PRINTS database.

data_1426.name: Phylogenetic continuous quantitative data
data_1426.definition: Continuous quantitative data that may be read during phylogenetic tree calculation.

data_1427.name: Phylogenetic discrete data
data_1427.definition: Character data with discrete states that may be read during phylogenetic tree calculation.

data_1428.name: Phylogenetic character cliques
data_1428.definition: One or more cliques of mutually compatible characters that are generated, for example from analysis of discrete character data, and are used to generate a phylogeny.

data_1429.name: Phylogenetic invariants
data_1429.definition: Phylogenetic invariants data for testing alternative tree topologies.

data_1438.name: Phylogenetic report
data_1438.definition:
A report of data concerning or derived from a phylogenetic tree, or from comparing two or more phylogenetic trees.
This is a broad data type and is used  for example for reports on confidence, shape or stratigraphic (age) data derived from phylogenetic tree analysis.

data_1439.name: DNA substitution model
data_1439.definition: A model of DNA substitution that explains a DNA sequence alignment, derived from phylogenetic tree analysis.

data_1440.name: Phylogenetic tree report (tree shape)
data_1440.definition: Data about the shape of a phylogenetic tree.

data_1441.name: Phylogenetic tree report (tree evaluation)
data_1441.definition: Data on the confidence of a phylogenetic tree.

data_1442.name: Phylogenetic tree distances
data_1442.definition: Distances, such as Branch Score distance, between two or more phylogenetic trees.

data_1443.name: Phylogenetic tree report (tree stratigraphic)
data_1443.definition: Molecular clock and stratigraphic (age) data derived from phylogenetic tree analysis.

data_1444.name: Phylogenetic character contrasts
data_1444.definition: Independent contrasts for characters used in a phylogenetic tree, or covariances, regressions and correlations between characters for those contrasts.

data_1446.name: Comparison matrix (integers)
data_1446.definition: Matrix of integer numbers for sequence comparison.

data_1447.name: Comparison matrix (floats)
data_1447.definition: Matrix of floating point numbers for sequence comparison.

data_1448.name: Comparison matrix (nucleotide)
data_1448.definition: Matrix of integer or floating point numbers for nucleotide comparison.

data_1449.name: Comparison matrix (amino acid)
data_1449.definition: Matrix of integer or floating point numbers for amino acid comparison.

data_1450.name: Nucleotide comparison matrix (integers)
data_1450.definition: Matrix of integer numbers for nucleotide comparison.

data_1451.name: Nucleotide comparison matrix (floats)
data_1451.definition: Matrix of floating point numbers for nucleotide comparison.

data_1452.name: Amino acid comparison matrix (integers)
data_1452.definition: Matrix of integer numbers for amino acid comparison.

data_1453.name: Amino acid comparison matrix (floats)
data_1453.definition: Matrix of floating point numbers for amino acid comparison.

data_1459.name: Nucleic acid structure
data_1459.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a nucleic acid tertiary (3D) structure.

data_1460.name: Protein structure
data_1460.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein tertiary (3D) structure, or part of a structure, possibly in complex with other molecules.

data_1461.name: Protein-ligand complex
data_1461.definition:
The structure of a protein in complex with a ligand, typically a small molecule such as an enzyme substrate or cofactor, but possibly another macromolecule.
This includes interactions of proteins with atoms, ions and small molecules or macromolecules such as nucleic acids or other polypeptides.  For stable inter-polypeptide interactions use 'Protein complex' instead.

data_1462.name: Carbohydrate structure
data_1462.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a carbohydrate (3D) structure.

data_1463.name: Small molecule structure
data_1463.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for the (3D) structure of a small molecule, such as any common chemical compound.

data_1464.name: DNA structure
data_1464.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a DNA tertiary (3D) structure.

data_1465.name: RNA structure
data_1465.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for an RNA tertiary (3D) structure.

data_1466.name: tRNA structure
data_1466.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a tRNA tertiary (3D) structure, including tmRNA, snoRNAs etc.

data_1467.name: Protein chain
data_1467.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for the tertiary (3D) structure of a polypeptide chain.

data_1468.name: Protein domain
data_1468.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for the tertiary (3D) structure of a protein domain.

data_1469.name: Protein structure (all atoms)
data_1469.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein tertiary (3D) structure (all atoms).

data_1470.name: C-alpha trace
data_1470.definition:
3D coordinate and associated data for a protein tertiary (3D) structure (typically C-alpha atoms only).
C-beta atoms from amino acid side-chains may be included.

data_1471.name: Protein chain (all atoms)
data_1471.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a polypeptide chain tertiary (3D) structure (all atoms).

data_1472.name: Protein chain (C-alpha atoms)
data_1472.definition:
3D coordinate and associated data for a polypeptide chain tertiary (3D) structure (typically C-alpha atoms only).
C-beta atoms from amino acid side-chains may be included.

data_1473.name: Protein domain (all atoms)
data_1473.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein domain tertiary (3D) structure (all atoms).

data_1474.name: Protein domain (C-alpha atoms)
data_1474.definition:
3D coordinate and associated data for a protein domain tertiary (3D) structure (typically C-alpha atoms only).
C-beta atoms from amino acid side-chains may be included.

data_1479.name: Structure alignment (pair)
data_1479.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two molecular tertiary (3D) structures.

data_1480.name: Structure alignment (multiple)
data_1480.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of more than two molecular tertiary (3D) structures.

data_1482.name: Nucleic acid structure alignment
data_1482.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of nucleic acid tertiary (3D) structures.

data_1483.name: Structure alignment (protein pair)
data_1483.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures.

data_1484.name: Multiple protein tertiary structure alignment
data_1484.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of more than two protein tertiary (3D) structures.

data_1485.name: Structure alignment (protein all atoms)
data_1485.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of protein tertiary (3D) structures (all atoms considered).

data_1486.name: Structure alignment (protein C-alpha atoms)
data_1486.definition:
Alignment (superimposition) of protein tertiary (3D) structures (typically C-alpha atoms only considered).
C-beta atoms from amino acid side-chains may be considered.

data_1487.name: Pairwise protein tertiary structure alignment (all atoms)
data_1487.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures (all atoms considered).

data_1488.name: Pairwise protein tertiary structure alignment (C-alpha atoms)
data_1488.definition:
Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures (typically C-alpha atoms only considered).
C-beta atoms from amino acid side-chains may be included.

data_1489.name: Multiple protein tertiary structure alignment (all atoms)
data_1489.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures (all atoms considered).

data_1490.name: Multiple protein tertiary structure alignment (C-alpha atoms)
data_1490.definition:
Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two protein tertiary (3D) structures (typically C-alpha atoms only considered).
C-beta atoms from amino acid side-chains may be included.

data_1491.name: Structure alignment (nucleic acid pair)
data_1491.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of exactly two nucleic acid tertiary (3D) structures.

data_1492.name: Multiple nucleic acid tertiary structure alignment
data_1492.definition: Alignment (superimposition) of more than two nucleic acid tertiary (3D) structures.

data_1494.name: Structural transformation matrix
data_1494.definition: Matrix to transform (rotate/translate) 3D coordinates, typically the transformation necessary to superimpose two molecular structures.

data_1495.name: DaliLite hit table
data_1495.definition:
DaliLite hit table of protein chain tertiary structure alignment data.
The significant and top-scoring hits for regions of the compared structures is shown. Data such as Z-Scores, number of aligned residues, root-mean-square deviation (RMSD) of atoms and sequence identity are given.

data_1496.name: Molecular similarity score
data_1496.definition: A score reflecting structural similarities of two molecules.

data_1497.name: Root-mean-square deviation
data_1497.definition: Root-mean-square deviation (RMSD) is calculated to measure the average distance between superimposed macromolecular coordinates.

data_1498.name: Tanimoto similarity score
data_1498.definition:
A measure of the similarity between two ligand fingerprints.
A ligand fingerprint is derived from ligand structural data from a Protein DataBank file. It reflects the elements or groups present or absent, covalent bonds and bond orders and the bonded environment in terms of SATIS codes and BLEEP atom types.

data_1499.name: 3D-1D scoring matrix
data_1499.definition: A matrix of 3D-1D scores reflecting the probability of amino acids to occur in different tertiary structural environments.

data_1501.name: Amino acid index
data_1501.definition: A table of 20 numerical values which quantify a property (e.g. physicochemical or biochemical) of the common amino acids.

data_1502.name: Amino acid index (chemical classes)
data_1502.definition: Chemical classification (small, aliphatic, aromatic, polar, charged etc) of amino acids.

data_1506.name: Amino acid index (hydropathy)
data_1506.definition: Hydrophobic, hydrophilic or charge properties of amino acids.

data_1507.name: Amino acid index (White-Wimley data)
data_1507.definition: Experimental free energy values for the water-interface and water-octanol transitions for the amino acids.

data_1508.name: Amino acid index (van der Waals radii)
data_1508.definition: Van der Waals radii of atoms for different amino acid residues.

data_1509.name: Enzyme report
data_1509.definition: An informative report on a specific enzyme.

data_1517.name: Restriction enzyme report
data_1517.definition:
An informative report on a specific restriction enzyme such as enzyme reference data.
This might include name of enzyme, organism, isoschizomers, methylation, source, suppliers, literature references, or data on restriction enzyme patterns such as name of enzyme, recognition site, length of pattern, number of cuts made by enzyme, details of blunt or sticky end cut etc.

data_1519.name: Peptide molecular weights
data_1519.definition:
List of molecular weight(s) of one or more proteins or peptides, for example cut by proteolytic enzymes or reagents.
The report might include associated data such as frequency of peptide fragment molecular weights.

data_1520.name: Peptide hydrophobic moment
data_1520.definition:
Report on the hydrophobic moment of a polypeptide sequence.
Hydrophobic moment is a peptides hydrophobicity measured for different angles of rotation.

data_1521.name: Protein aliphatic index
data_1521.definition:
The aliphatic index of a protein.
The aliphatic index is the relative protein volume occupied by aliphatic side chains.

data_1522.name: Protein sequence hydropathy plot
data_1522.definition:
A protein sequence with annotation on hydrophobic or hydrophilic / charged regions, hydrophobicity plot etc.
Hydrophobic moment is a peptides hydrophobicity measured for different angles of rotation.

data_1523.name: Protein charge plot
data_1523.definition: A plot of the mean charge of the amino acids within a window of specified length as the window is moved along a protein sequence.

data_1524.name: Protein solubility
data_1524.definition: The solubility or atomic solvation energy of a protein sequence or structure.

data_1525.name: Protein crystallizability
data_1525.definition: Data on the crystallizability of a protein sequence.

data_1526.name: Protein globularity
data_1526.definition: Data on the stability, intrinsic disorder or globularity of a protein sequence.

data_1527.name: Protein titration curve
data_1527.definition: The titration curve of a protein.

data_1528.name: Protein isoelectric point
data_1528.definition: The isoelectric point of one proteins.

data_1529.name: Protein pKa value
data_1529.definition: The pKa value of a protein.

data_1530.name: Protein hydrogen exchange rate
data_1530.definition: The hydrogen exchange rate of a protein.

data_1531.name: Protein extinction coefficient
data_1531.definition: The extinction coefficient of a protein.

data_1532.name: Protein optical density
data_1532.definition: The optical density of a protein.

data_1533.name: Protein subcellular localisation
data_1533.definition: An informative report on protein subcellular localisation (nuclear, cytoplasmic, mitochondrial, chloroplast, plastid, membrane etc) or destination (exported / extracellular proteins).

data_1534.name: Peptide immunogenicity data
data_1534.definition:
An report on allergenicity / immunogenicity of peptides and proteins.
This includes data on peptide ligands that elicit an immune response (immunogens), allergic cross-reactivity, predicted antigenicity (Hopp and Woods plot) etc. These data are useful in the development of peptide-specific antibodies or multi-epitope vaccines. Methods might use sequence data (for example motifs) and / or structural data.

data_1536.name: MHC peptide immunogenicity report
data_1536.definition: A report on the immunogenicity of MHC class I or class II binding peptides.

data_1537.name: Protein structure report
data_1537.definition: A human-readable collection of information about one or more specific protein 3D structure(s) or structural domains.

data_1539.name: Protein structural quality report
data_1539.definition:
Report on the quality of a protein three-dimensional model.
Model validation might involve checks for atomic packing, steric clashes, agreement with electron density maps etc.

data_1540.name: Protein non-covalent interactions report
data_1540.definition: Data on inter-atomic or inter-residue contacts, distances and interactions in protein structure(s) or on the interactions of protein atoms or residues with non-protein groups.

data_1541.name: Protein flexibility or motion report
data_1541.definition:
Informative report on flexibility or motion of a protein structure.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_1542.name: Protein solvent accessibility
data_1542.definition:
Data on the solvent accessible or buried surface area of a protein structure.
This concept covers definitions of the protein surface, interior and interfaces, accessible and buried residues, surface accessible pockets, interior inaccessible cavities etc.

data_1543.name: Protein surface report
data_1543.definition:
Data on the surface properties (shape, hydropathy, electrostatic patches etc) of a protein structure.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_1544.name: Ramachandran plot
data_1544.definition: Phi/psi angle data or a Ramachandran plot of a protein structure.

data_1545.name: Protein dipole moment
data_1545.definition: Data on the net charge distribution (dipole moment) of a protein structure.

data_1546.name: Protein distance matrix
data_1546.definition: A matrix of distances between amino acid residues (for example the C-alpha atoms) in a protein structure.

data_1547.name: Protein contact map
data_1547.definition: An amino acid residue contact map for a protein structure.

data_1548.name: Protein residue 3D cluster
data_1548.definition: Report on clusters of contacting residues in protein structures such as a key structural residue network.

data_1549.name: Protein hydrogen bonds
data_1549.definition: Patterns of hydrogen bonding in protein structures.

data_1550.name: Protein non-canonical interactions
data_1550.definition: Non-canonical atomic interactions in protein structures.

data_1553.name: CATH node
data_1553.definition:
Information on a node from the CATH database.
The report (for example http://www.cathdb.info/cathnode/1.10.10.10) includes CATH code (of the node and upper levels in the hierarchy), classification text (of appropriate levels in hierarchy), list of child nodes, representative domain and other relevant data and links.

data_1554.name: SCOP node
data_1554.definition: Information on a node from the SCOP database.

data_1555.name: EMBASSY domain classification
data_1555.definition: An EMBASSY domain classification file (DCF) of classification and other data for domains from SCOP or CATH, in EMBL-like format.

data_1556.name: CATH class
data_1556.definition: Information on a protein 'class' node from the CATH database.

data_1557.name: CATH architecture
data_1557.definition: Information on a protein 'architecture' node from the CATH database.

data_1558.name: CATH topology
data_1558.definition: Information on a protein 'topology' node from the CATH database.

data_1559.name: CATH homologous superfamily
data_1559.definition: Information on a protein 'homologous superfamily' node from the CATH database.

data_1560.name: CATH structurally similar group
data_1560.definition: Information on a protein 'structurally similar group' node from the CATH database.

data_1561.name: CATH functional category
data_1561.definition: Information on a protein 'functional category' node from the CATH database.

data_1564.name: Protein fold recognition report
data_1564.definition:
A report on known protein structural domains or folds that are recognised (identified) in protein sequence(s).
Methods use some type of mapping between sequence and fold, for example secondary structure prediction and alignment, profile comparison, sequence properties, homologous sequence search, kernel machines etc. Domains and folds might be taken from SCOP or CATH.

data_1565.name: Protein-protein interaction report
data_1565.definition: protein-protein interaction(s), including interactions between protein domains.

data_1566.name: Protein-ligand interaction report
data_1566.definition: An informative report on protein-ligand (small molecule) interaction(s).

data_1583.name: Nucleic acid melting profile
data_1583.definition:
Data on the dissociation characteristics of a double-stranded nucleic acid molecule (DNA or a DNA/RNA hybrid) during heating.
A melting (stability) profile calculated the free energy required to unwind and separate the nucleic acid strands, plotted for sliding windows over a sequence.

data_1584.name: Nucleic acid enthalpy
data_1584.definition: Enthalpy of hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA).

data_1585.name: Nucleic acid entropy
data_1585.definition: Entropy of hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA).

data_1586.name: Nucleic acid melting temperature
data_1586.definition: Melting temperature of hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA).

data_1587.name: Nucleic acid stitch profile
data_1587.definition: Stitch profile of hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA).

data_1588.name: DNA base pair stacking energies data
data_1588.definition: DNA base pair stacking energies data.

data_1589.name: DNA base pair twist angle data
data_1589.definition: DNA base pair twist angle data.

data_1590.name: DNA base trimer roll angles data
data_1590.definition: DNA base trimer roll angles data.

data_1591.name: Vienna RNA parameters
data_1591.definition: RNA parameters used by the Vienna package.

data_1592.name: Vienna RNA structure constraints
data_1592.definition: Structure constraints used by the Vienna package.

data_1593.name: Vienna RNA concentration data
data_1593.definition: RNA concentration data used by the Vienna package.

data_1594.name: Vienna RNA calculated energy
data_1594.definition: RNA calculated energy data generated by the Vienna package.

data_1595.name: Base pairing probability matrix dotplot
data_1595.definition:
Dotplot of RNA base pairing probability matrix.
Such as generated by the Vienna package.

data_1596.name: Nucleic acid folding report
data_1596.definition: A human-readable collection of information about RNA/DNA folding, minimum folding energies for DNA or RNA sequences, energy landscape of RNA mutants etc.

data_1597.name: Codon usage table
data_1597.definition:
Table of codon usage data calculated from one or more nucleic acid sequences.
A codon usage table might include the codon usage table name, optional comments and a table with columns for codons and corresponding codon usage data. A genetic code can be extracted from or represented by a codon usage table.

data_1598.name: Genetic code
data_1598.definition:
A genetic code for an organism.
A genetic code need not include detailed codon usage information.

data_1599.name: Codon adaptation index
data_1599.definition: A simple measure of synonymous codon usage bias often used to predict gene expression levels.

data_1600.name: Codon usage bias plot
data_1600.definition: A plot of the synonymous codon usage calculated for windows over a nucleotide sequence.

data_1601.name: Nc statistic
data_1601.definition: The effective number of codons used in a gene sequence.  This reflects how far codon usage of a gene departs from equal usage of synonymous codons.

data_1602.name: Codon usage fraction difference
data_1602.definition: The differences in codon usage fractions between two codon usage tables.

data_1621.name: Pharmacogenomic test report
data_1621.definition:
A human-readable collection of information about the influence of genotype on drug response.
The report might correlate gene expression or single-nucleotide polymorphisms with drug efficacy or toxicity.

data_1622.name: Disease report
data_1622.definition:
A human-readable collection of information about a specific disease.
For example, an informative report on a specific tumor including nature and origin of the sample, anatomic site, organ or tissue, tumor type, including morphology and/or histologic type, and so on.

data_1634.name: Linkage disequilibrium (report)
data_1634.definition: A report on linkage disequilibrium; the non-random association of alleles or polymorphisms at two or more loci (not necessarily on the same chromosome).

data_1636.name: Heat map
data_1636.definition: A graphical 2D tabular representation of expression data, typically derived from an omics experiment. A heat map is a table where rows and columns correspond to different features and contexts (for example, cells or samples) and the cell colour represents the level of expression of a gene that context.

data_1642.name: Affymetrix probe sets library file
data_1642.definition: Affymetrix library file of information about which probes belong to which probe set.

data_1643.name: Affymetrix probe sets information library file
data_1643.definition: Affymetrix library file of information about the probe sets such as the gene name with which the probe set is associated.

data_1646.name: Molecular weights standard fingerprint
data_1646.definition: Standard protonated molecular masses from trypsin (modified porcine trypsin, Promega) and keratin peptides, used in EMBOSS.

data_1656.name: Metabolic pathway report
data_1656.definition:
A report typically including a map (diagram) of a metabolic pathway.
This includes carbohydrate, energy, lipid, nucleotide, amino acid, glycan, PK/NRP, cofactor/vitamin, secondary metabolite, xenobiotics etc.

data_1659.name: Signal transduction pathway report
data_1659.definition: A report typically including a map (diagram) of a signal transduction pathway.

data_1661.name: Disease pathway or network report
data_1661.definition: disease pathways, typically of human disease.

data_1662.name: Drug structure relationship map
data_1662.definition: A report typically including a map (diagram) of drug structure relationships.

data_1664.name: MIRIAM datatype
data_1664.definition:
An entry (data type) from the Minimal Information Requested in the Annotation of Biochemical Models (MIRIAM) database of data resources.
A MIRIAM entry describes a MIRIAM data type including the official name, synonyms, root URI, identifier pattern (regular expression applied to a unique identifier of the data type) and documentation. Each data type can be associated with several resources. Each resource is a physical location of a service (typically a database) providing information on the elements of a data type. Several resources may exist for each data type, provided the same (mirrors) or different information. MIRIAM provides a stable and persistent reference to its data types.

data_1667.name: E-value
data_1667.definition:
A simple floating point number defining the lower or upper limit of an expectation value (E-value).
An expectation value (E-Value) is the expected number of observations which are at least as extreme as observations expected to occur by random chance. The E-value describes the number of hits with a given score or better that are expected to occur at random when searching a database of a particular size. It decreases exponentially with the score (S) of a hit. A low E value indicates a more significant score.

data_1668.name: Z-value
data_1668.definition:
The z-value is the number of standard deviations a data value is above or below a mean value.
A z-value might be specified as a threshold for reporting hits from database searches.

data_1669.name: P-value
data_1669.definition:
The P-value is the probability of obtaining by random chance a result that is at least as extreme as an observed result, assuming a NULL hypothesis is true.
A z-value might be specified as a threshold for reporting hits from database searches.

data_1670.name: Database version information
data_1670.definition: Information on a database (or ontology) version, for example name, version number and release date.

data_1671.name: Tool version information
data_1671.definition: Information on an application version, for example name, version number and release date.

data_1672.name: CATH version information
data_1672.definition: Information on a version of the CATH database.

data_1673.name: Swiss-Prot to PDB mapping
data_1673.definition: Cross-mapping of Swiss-Prot codes to PDB identifiers.

data_1674.name: Sequence database cross-references
data_1674.definition: Cross-references from a sequence record to other databases.

data_1675.name: Job status
data_1675.definition:
Metadata on the status of a submitted job.
Values for EBI services are 'DONE' (job has finished and the results can then be retrieved), 'ERROR' (the job failed or no results where found), 'NOT_FOUND' (the job id is no longer available; job results might be deleted, 'PENDING' (the job is in a queue waiting processing), 'RUNNING' (the job is currently being processed).

data_1676.name: Job ID
data_1676.definition: The (typically numeric) unique identifier of a submitted job.

data_1677.name: Job type
data_1677.definition: A label (text token) describing the type of job, for example interactive or non-interactive.

data_1678.name: Tool log
data_1678.definition: A report of tool-specific metadata on some analysis or process performed, for example a log of diagnostic or error messages.

data_1679.name: DaliLite log file
data_1679.definition: DaliLite log file describing all the steps taken by a DaliLite alignment of two protein structures.

data_1689.name: Username
data_1689.definition: A username on a computer system.

data_1690.name: Password
data_1690.definition: A password on a computer system.

data_1691.name: Email address
data_1691.definition: A valid email address of an end-user.

data_1693.name: Number of iterations
data_1693.definition: Number of iterations of an algorithm.

data_1694.name: Number of output entities
data_1694.definition: Number of entities (for example database hits, sequences, alignments etc) to write to an output file.

data_1695.name: Hit sort order
data_1695.definition: Controls the order of hits (reported matches) in an output file from a database search.

data_1696.name: Drug report
data_1696.definition: A human-readable collection of information about a specific drug.

data_1707.name: Phylogenetic tree image
data_1707.definition:
An image (for viewing or printing) of a phylogenetic tree including (typically) a plot of rooted or unrooted phylogenies, cladograms, circular trees or phenograms and associated information.
See also 'Phylogenetic tree'

data_1708.name: RNA secondary structure image
data_1708.definition: Image of RNA secondary structure, knots, pseudoknots etc.

data_1710.name: Structure image
data_1710.definition: Image of one or more molecular tertiary (3D) structures.

data_1711.name: Sequence alignment image
data_1711.definition: Image of two or more aligned molecular sequences possibly annotated with alignment features.

data_1712.name: Chemical structure image
data_1712.definition:
An image of the structure of a small chemical compound.
The molecular identifier and formula are typically included.

data_1713.name: Fate map
data_1713.definition: A fate map is a plan of early stage of an embryo such as a blastula, showing areas that are significance to development.

data_1714.name: Microarray spots image
data_1714.definition: An image of spots from a microarray experiment.

data_1715.name: BioPax term
data_1715.definition: A term from the BioPax ontology.

data_1716.name: GO
data_1716.definition: A term definition from The Gene Ontology (GO).

data_1717.name: MeSH
data_1717.definition: A term from the MeSH vocabulary.

data_1718.name: HGNC
data_1718.definition: A term from the HGNC controlled vocabulary.

data_1719.name: NCBI taxonomy vocabulary
data_1719.definition: A term from the NCBI taxonomy vocabulary.

data_1720.name: Plant ontology term
data_1720.definition: A term from the Plant Ontology (PO).

data_1721.name: UMLS
data_1721.definition: A term from the UMLS vocabulary.

data_1722.name: FMA
data_1722.definition:
A term from Foundational Model of Anatomy.
Classifies anatomical entities according to their shared characteristics (genus) and distinguishing characteristics (differentia). Specifies the part-whole and spatial relationships of the entities, morphological transformation of the entities during prenatal development and the postnatal life cycle and principles, rules and definitions according to which classes and relationships in the other three components of FMA are represented.

data_1723.name: EMAP
data_1723.definition: A term from the EMAP mouse ontology.

data_1724.name: ChEBI
data_1724.definition: A term from the ChEBI ontology.

data_1725.name: MGED
data_1725.definition: A term from the MGED ontology.

data_1726.name: myGrid
data_1726.definition:
A term from the myGrid ontology.
The ontology is provided as two components, the service ontology and the domain ontology. The domain ontology acts provides concepts for core bioinformatics data types and their relations. The service ontology describes the physical and operational features of web services.

data_1727.name: GO (biological process)
data_1727.definition:
A term definition for a biological process from the Gene Ontology (GO).
Data Type is an enumerated string.

data_1728.name: GO (molecular function)
data_1728.definition:
A term definition for a molecular function from the Gene Ontology (GO).
Data Type is an enumerated string.

data_1729.name: GO (cellular component)
data_1729.definition:
A term definition for a cellular component from the Gene Ontology (GO).
Data Type is an enumerated string.

data_1730.name: Ontology relation type
data_1730.definition: A relation type defined in an ontology.

data_1731.name: Ontology concept definition
data_1731.definition: The definition of a concept from an ontology.

data_1732.name: Ontology concept comment
data_1732.definition: A comment on a concept from an ontology.

data_1733.name: Ontology concept reference
data_1733.definition: Reference for a concept from an ontology.

data_1738.name: doc2loc document information
data_1738.definition:
Information on a published article provided by the doc2loc program.
The doc2loc output includes the url, format, type and availability code of a document for every service provider.

data_1742.name: PDB residue number
data_1742.definition: A residue identifier (a string) from a PDB file.

data_1743.name: Atomic coordinate
data_1743.definition: Cartesian coordinate of an atom (in a molecular structure).

data_1744.name: Atomic x coordinate
data_1744.definition: Cartesian x coordinate of an atom (in a molecular structure).

data_1745.name: Atomic y coordinate
data_1745.definition: Cartesian y coordinate of an atom (in a molecular structure).

data_1746.name: Atomic z coordinate
data_1746.definition: Cartesian z coordinate of an atom (in a molecular structure).

data_1748.name: PDB atom name
data_1748.definition: Identifier (a string) of a specific atom from a PDB file for a molecular structure.

data_1755.name: Protein atom
data_1755.definition:
Data on a single atom from a protein structure.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_1756.name: Protein residue
data_1756.definition:
Data on a single amino acid residue position in a protein structure.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_1758.name: PDB residue name
data_1758.definition: Three-letter amino acid residue names as used in PDB files.

data_1759.name: PDB model number
data_1759.definition: Identifier of a model structure from a PDB file.

data_1762.name: CATH domain report
data_1762.definition:
Summary of domain classification information for a CATH domain.
The report (for example http://www.cathdb.info/domain/1cukA01) includes CATH codes for levels in the hierarchy for the domain, level descriptions and relevant data and links.

data_1764.name: CATH representative domain sequences (ATOM)
data_1764.definition: FASTA sequence database (based on ATOM records in PDB) for CATH domains (clustered at different levels of sequence identity).

data_1765.name: CATH representative domain sequences (COMBS)
data_1765.definition: FASTA sequence database (based on COMBS sequence data) for CATH domains (clustered at different levels of sequence identity).

data_1766.name: CATH domain sequences (ATOM)
data_1766.definition: FASTA sequence database for all CATH domains (based on PDB ATOM records).

data_1767.name: CATH domain sequences (COMBS)
data_1767.definition: FASTA sequence database for all CATH domains (based on COMBS sequence data).

data_1771.name: Sequence version
data_1771.definition: Information on an molecular sequence version.

data_1772.name: Score
data_1772.definition: A numerical value, that is some type of scored value arising for example from a prediction method.

data_1776.name: Protein report (function)
data_1776.definition:
Report on general functional properties of specific protein(s).
For properties that can be mapped to a sequence, use 'Sequence report' instead.

data_1783.name: Gene name (ASPGD)
data_1783.definition: Name of a gene from Aspergillus Genome Database.

data_1784.name: Gene name (CGD)
data_1784.definition: Name of a gene from Candida Genome Database.

data_1785.name: Gene name (dictyBase)
data_1785.definition: Name of a gene from dictyBase database.

data_1786.name: Gene name (EcoGene primary)
data_1786.definition: Primary name of a gene from EcoGene Database.

data_1787.name: Gene name (MaizeGDB)
data_1787.definition: Name of a gene from MaizeGDB (maize genes) database.

data_1788.name: Gene name (SGD)
data_1788.definition: Name of a gene from Saccharomyces Genome Database.

data_1789.name: Gene name (TGD)
data_1789.definition: Name of a gene from Tetrahymena Genome Database.

data_1790.name: Gene name (CGSC)
data_1790.definition: Symbol of a gene from E.coli Genetic Stock Center.

data_1791.name: Gene name (HGNC)
data_1791.definition: Symbol of a gene approved by the HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee.

data_1792.name: Gene name (MGD)
data_1792.definition: Symbol of a gene from the Mouse Genome Database.

data_1793.name: Gene name (Bacillus subtilis)
data_1793.definition: Symbol of a gene from Bacillus subtilis Genome Sequence Project.

data_1794.name: Gene ID (PlasmoDB)
data_1794.definition: Identifier of a gene from PlasmoDB Plasmodium Genome Resource.

data_1795.name: Gene ID (EcoGene)
data_1795.definition: Identifier of a gene from EcoGene Database.

data_1797.name: Gene ID (GeneDB Glossina morsitans)
data_1797.definition: Gene identifier from Glossina morsitans GeneDB database.

data_1798.name: Gene ID (GeneDB Leishmania major)
data_1798.definition: Gene identifier from Leishmania major GeneDB database.

data_1799.name: Gene ID (GeneDB Plasmodium falciparum)
data_1799.definition: Gene identifier from Plasmodium falciparum GeneDB database.

data_1800.name: Gene ID (GeneDB Schizosaccharomyces pombe)
data_1800.definition: Gene identifier from Schizosaccharomyces pombe GeneDB database.

data_1801.name: Gene ID (GeneDB Trypanosoma brucei)
data_1801.definition: Gene identifier from Trypanosoma brucei GeneDB database.

data_1803.name: Gene ID (Virginia microbial)
data_1803.definition: Gene identifier from Virginia Bioinformatics Institute microbial database.

data_1804.name: Gene ID (SGN)
data_1804.definition: Gene identifier from Sol Genomics Network.

data_1805.name: Gene ID (WormBase)
data_1805.definition: Gene identifier used by WormBase database.

data_1806.name: Gene synonym
data_1806.definition: Any name (other than the recommended one) for a gene.

data_1807.name: ORF name
data_1807.definition: The name of an open reading frame attributed by a sequencing project.

data_1852.name: Sequence assembly component
data_1852.definition: A component of a larger sequence assembly.

data_1853.name: Chromosome annotation (aberration)
data_1853.definition: A report on a chromosome aberration such as abnormalities in chromosome structure.

data_1855.name: Clone ID
data_1855.definition: An identifier of a clone (cloned molecular sequence) from a database.

data_1856.name: PDB insertion code
data_1856.definition: An insertion code (part of the residue number) for an amino acid residue from a PDB file.

data_1857.name: Atomic occupancy
data_1857.definition:
The fraction of an atom type present at a site in a molecular structure.
The sum of the occupancies of all the atom types at a site should not normally significantly exceed 1.0.

data_1858.name: Isotropic B factor
data_1858.definition: Isotropic B factor (atomic displacement parameter) for an atom from a PDB file.

data_1859.name: Deletion map
data_1859.definition:
A cytogenetic map showing chromosome banding patterns in mutant cell lines relative to the wild type.
A cytogenetic map is built from a set of mutant cell lines with sub-chromosomal deletions and a reference wild-type line ('genome deletion panel'). The panel is used to map markers onto the genome by comparing mutant to wild-type banding patterns. Markers are linked (occur in the same deleted region) if they share the same banding pattern (presence or absence) as the deletion panel.

data_1860.name: QTL map
data_1860.definition: A genetic map which shows the approximate location of quantitative trait loci (QTL) between two or more markers.

data_1863.name: Haplotype map
data_1863.definition: A map of haplotypes in a genome or other sequence, describing common patterns of genetic variation.

data_1864.name: Map set data
data_1864.definition: Data describing a set of multiple genetic or physical maps, typically sharing a common set of features which are mapped.

data_1865.name: Map feature
data_1865.definition:
A feature which may mapped (positioned) on a genetic or other type of map.
Mappable features may be based on Gramene's notion of map features; see http://www.gramene.org/db/cmap/feature_type_info.

data_1866.name: Map type
data_1866.definition:
A designation of the type of map (genetic map, physical map, sequence map etc) or map set.
Map types may be based on Gramene's notion of a map type; see http://www.gramene.org/db/cmap/map_type_info.

data_1867.name: Protein fold name
data_1867.definition: The name of a protein fold.

data_1868.name: Taxon
data_1868.definition:
The name of a group of organisms belonging to the same taxonomic rank.
For a complete list of taxonomic ranks see https://www.phenoscape.org/wiki/Taxonomic_Rank_Vocabulary.

data_1869.name: Organism identifier
data_1869.definition: A unique identifier of a (group of) organisms.

data_1870.name: Genus name
data_1870.definition: The name of a genus of organism.

data_1872.name: Taxonomic classification
data_1872.definition:
The full name for a group of organisms, reflecting their biological classification and (usually) conforming to a standard nomenclature.
Name components correspond to levels in a taxonomic hierarchy (e.g. 'Genus', 'Species', etc.) Meta information such as a reference where the name was defined and a date might be included.

data_1873.name: iHOP organism ID
data_1873.definition: A unique identifier for an organism used in the iHOP database.

data_1874.name: Genbank common name
data_1874.definition: Common name for an organism as used in the GenBank database.

data_1875.name: NCBI taxon
data_1875.definition: The name of a taxon from the NCBI taxonomy database.

data_1878.name: Misspelling
data_1878.definition: A common misspelling of a word.

data_1879.name: Acronym
data_1879.definition: An abbreviation of a phrase or word.

data_1880.name: Misnomer
data_1880.definition: A term which is likely to be misleading of its meaning.

data_1881.name: Author ID
data_1881.definition: Information on the authors of a published work.

data_1882.name: DragonDB author identifier
data_1882.definition: An identifier representing an author in the DragonDB database.

data_1883.name: Annotated URI
data_1883.definition: A URI along with annotation describing the data found at the address.

data_1884.name: UniProt keywords
data_1884.definition: A controlled vocabulary for words and phrases that can appear in the keywords field (KW line) of entries from the UniProt database.

data_1885.name: Gene ID (GeneFarm)
data_1885.definition: Identifier of a gene from the GeneFarm database.

data_1886.name: Blattner number
data_1886.definition: The blattner identifier for a gene.

data_1887.name: Gene ID (MIPS Maize)
data_1887.definition: Identifier for genetic elements in MIPS Maize database.

data_1888.name: Gene ID (MIPS Medicago)
data_1888.definition: Identifier for genetic elements in MIPS Medicago database.

data_1889.name: Gene name (DragonDB)
data_1889.definition: The name of an Antirrhinum Gene from the DragonDB database.

data_1890.name: Gene name (Arabidopsis)
data_1890.definition: A unique identifier for an Arabidopsis gene, which is an acronym or abbreviation of the gene name.

data_1891.name: iHOP symbol
data_1891.definition: A unique identifier of a protein or gene used in the iHOP database.

data_1892.name: Gene name (GeneFarm)
data_1892.definition: Name of a gene from the GeneFarm database.

data_1893.name: Locus ID
data_1893.definition: A unique name or other identifier of a genetic locus, typically conforming to a scheme that names loci (such as predicted genes) depending on their position in a molecular sequence, for example a completely sequenced genome or chromosome.

data_1895.name: Locus ID (AGI)
data_1895.definition: Locus identifier for Arabidopsis Genome Initiative (TAIR, TIGR and MIPS databases)

data_1896.name: Locus ID (ASPGD)
data_1896.definition: Identifier for loci from ASPGD (Aspergillus Genome Database).

data_1897.name: Locus ID (MGG)
data_1897.definition: Identifier for loci from Magnaporthe grisea Database at the Broad Institute.

data_1898.name: Locus ID (CGD)
data_1898.definition: Identifier for loci from CGD (Candida Genome Database).

data_1899.name: Locus ID (CMR)
data_1899.definition: Locus identifier for Comprehensive Microbial Resource at the J. Craig Venter Institute.

data_1900.name: NCBI locus tag
data_1900.definition: Identifier for loci from NCBI database.

data_1901.name: Locus ID (SGD)
data_1901.definition: Identifier for loci from SGD (Saccharomyces Genome Database).

data_1902.name: Locus ID (MMP)
data_1902.definition: Identifier of loci from Maize Mapping Project.

data_1903.name: Locus ID (DictyBase)
data_1903.definition: Identifier of locus from DictyBase (Dictyostelium discoideum).

data_1904.name: Locus ID (EntrezGene)
data_1904.definition: Identifier of a locus from EntrezGene database.

data_1905.name: Locus ID (MaizeGDB)
data_1905.definition: Identifier of locus from MaizeGDB (Maize genome database).

data_1906.name: Quantitative trait locus
data_1906.definition:
A stretch of DNA that is closely linked to the genes underlying a quantitative trait (a phenotype that varies in degree and depends upon the interactions between multiple genes and their environment).
A QTL sometimes but does not necessarily correspond to a gene.

data_1907.name: Gene ID (KOME)
data_1907.definition: Identifier of a gene from the KOME database.

data_1908.name: Locus ID (Tropgene)
data_1908.definition: Identifier of a locus from the Tropgene database.

data_1916.name: Alignment
data_1916.definition: An alignment of molecular sequences, structures or profiles derived from them.

data_1917.name: Atomic property
data_1917.definition: Data for an atom (in a molecular structure).

data_2007.name: UniProt keyword
data_2007.definition: A word or phrase that can appear in the keywords field (KW line) of entries from the UniProt database.

data_2009.name: Ordered locus name
data_2009.definition: A name for a genetic locus conforming to a scheme that names loci (such as predicted genes) depending on their position in a molecular sequence, for example a completely sequenced genome or chromosome.

data_2012.name: Sequence coordinates
data_2012.definition:
A position in a map (for example a genetic map), either a single position (point) or a region / interval.
This includes positions in genomes based on a reference sequence. A position may be specified for any mappable object, i.e. anything that may have positional information such as a physical position in a chromosome. Data might include sequence region name, strand, coordinate system name, assembly name, start position and end position.

data_2016.name: Amino acid property
data_2016.definition: Data concerning the intrinsic physical (e.g. structural) or chemical properties of one, more or all amino acids.

data_2018.name: Annotation
data_2018.definition:
A human-readable collection of information which (typically) is generated or collated by hand and which describes a biological entity, phenomena or associated primary (e.g. sequence or structural) data, as distinct from the primary data itself and computer-generated reports derived from it.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2019.name: Map data
data_2019.definition: Data describing a molecular map (genetic or physical) or a set of such maps, including various attributes of, data extracted from or derived from the analysis of them, but exluding the map(s) themselves. This  includes metadata for map sets that share a common set of features which are mapped.

data_2022.name: Vienna RNA structural data
data_2022.definition: Data used by the Vienna RNA analysis package.

data_2023.name: Sequence mask parameter
data_2023.definition: Data used to replace (mask) characters in a molecular sequence.

data_2024.name: Enzyme kinetics data
data_2024.definition:
Data concerning chemical reaction(s) catalysed by enzyme(s).
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2025.name: Michaelis Menten plot
data_2025.definition: A plot giving an approximation of the kinetics of an enzyme-catalysed reaction, assuming simple kinetics (i.e. no intermediate or product inhibition, allostericity or cooperativity). It plots initial reaction rate to the substrate concentration (S) from which the maximum rate (vmax) is apparent.

data_2026.name: Hanes Woolf plot
data_2026.definition: A plot based on the Michaelis Menten equation of enzyme kinetics plotting the ratio of the initial substrate concentration (S) against the reaction velocity (v).

data_2028.name: Experimental data
data_2028.definition:
Raw data from or annotation on laboratory experiments.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_2042.name: Evidence
data_2042.definition: Typically a human-readable summary of body of facts or information indicating why a statement is true or valid. This may include a computational prediction, laboratory experiment, literature reference etc.

data_2043.name: Sequence record lite
data_2043.definition: A molecular sequence and minimal metadata, typically an identifier of the sequence and/or a comment.

data_2044.name: Sequence
data_2044.definition:
One or more molecular sequences, possibly with associated annotation.
This concept is a placeholder of concepts for primary sequence data including raw sequences and sequence records.  It should not normally be used for derivatives such as sequence alignments, motifs or profiles.

data_2046.name: Nucleic acid sequence record (lite)
data_2046.definition: A nucleic acid sequence and minimal metadata, typically an identifier of the sequence and/or a comment.

data_2047.name: Protein sequence record (lite)
data_2047.definition: A protein sequence and minimal metadata, typically an identifier of the sequence and/or a comment.

data_2048.name: Report
data_2048.definition:
A human-readable collection of information including annotation on a biological entity or phenomena, computer-generated reports of analysis of primary data (e.g. sequence or structural), and metadata (data about primary data) or any other free (essentially unformatted) text, as distinct from the primary data itself.
You can use this term by default for any textual report, in case you can't find another, more specific term. Reports may be generated automatically or collated by hand and can include metadata on the origin, source, history, ownership or location of some thing.

data_2053.name: Structural data
data_2053.definition:
Data concerning molecular structural data.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2079.name: Search parameter
data_2079.definition: Some simple value controlling a search operation, typically a search of a database.

data_2080.name: Database search results
data_2080.definition: A report of hits from searching a database of some type.

data_2081.name: Secondary structure
data_2081.definition: The secondary structure assignment (predicted or real) of a nucleic acid or protein.

data_2082.name: Matrix
data_2082.definition:
An array of numerical values.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2083.name: Alignment data
data_2083.definition:
Data concerning, extracted from, or derived from the analysis of molecular alignment of some type.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2084.name: Nucleic acid report
data_2084.definition: A human-readable collection of information about one or more specific nucleic acid molecules.

data_2085.name: Structure report
data_2085.definition: A human-readable collection of information about one or more molecular tertiary (3D) structures.  It might include annotation on the structure, a computer-generated report of analysis of structural data, and metadata (data about primary data) or any other free (essentially unformatted) text, as distinct from the primary data itself.

data_2086.name: Nucleic acid structure data
data_2086.definition: A report on nucleic acid structure-derived data, describing structural properties of a DNA molecule, or any other annotation or information about specific nucleic acid 3D structure(s).

data_2087.name: Molecular property
data_2087.definition: A report on the physical (e.g. structural) or chemical properties of molecules, or parts of a molecule.

data_2088.name: DNA base structural data
data_2088.definition: Structural data for DNA base pairs or runs of bases, such as energy or angle data.

data_2090.name: Database entry version information
data_2090.definition: Information on a database (or ontology) entry version, such as name (or other identifier) or parent database, unique identifier of entry, data, author and so on.

data_2091.name: Accession
data_2091.definition: A persistent (stable) and unique identifier, typically identifying an object (entry) from a database.

data_2092.name: SNP
data_2092.definition: single nucleotide polymorphism (SNP) in a DNA sequence.

data_2093.name: Data reference
data_2093.definition:
Reference to a dataset (or a cross-reference between two datasets), typically one or more entries in a biological database or ontology.
A list of database accessions or identifiers are usually included.

data_2098.name: Job identifier
data_2098.definition: An identifier of a submitted job.

data_2099.name: Name
data_2099.definition: A name of a thing, which need not necessarily uniquely identify it.

data_2100.name: Type
data_2100.definition: A label (text token) describing the type of a thing, typically an enumerated string (a string with one of a limited set of values).

data_2101.name: User ID
data_2101.definition: An identifier of a software end-user (typically a person).

data_2102.name: KEGG organism code
data_2102.definition: A three-letter code used in the KEGG databases to uniquely identify organisms.

data_2103.name: Gene name (KEGG GENES)
data_2103.definition: Name of an entry (gene) from the KEGG GENES database.

data_2104.name: BioCyc ID
data_2104.definition: Identifier of an object from one of the BioCyc databases.

data_2105.name: Compound ID (BioCyc)
data_2105.definition: Identifier of a compound from the BioCyc chemical compounds database.

data_2106.name: Reaction ID (BioCyc)
data_2106.definition: Identifier of a biological reaction from the BioCyc reactions database.

data_2107.name: Enzyme ID (BioCyc)
data_2107.definition: Identifier of an enzyme from the BioCyc enzymes database.

data_2108.name: Reaction ID
data_2108.definition: Identifier of a biological reaction from a database.

data_2109.name: Identifier (hybrid)
data_2109.definition:
An identifier that is re-used for data objects of fundamentally different types (typically served from a single database).
This branch provides an alternative organisation of the concepts nested under 'Accession' and 'Name'. All concepts under here are already included under 'Accession' or 'Name'.

data_2111.name: Codon usage table ID
data_2111.definition: Identifier of a codon usage table, for example a genetic code.

data_2112.name: FlyBase primary identifier
data_2112.definition: Primary identifier of an object from the FlyBase database.

data_2113.name: WormBase identifier
data_2113.definition: Identifier of an object from the WormBase database.

data_2114.name: WormBase wormpep ID
data_2114.definition: Protein identifier used by WormBase database.

data_2116.name: Nucleic acid features (codon)
data_2116.definition: An informative report on a trinucleotide sequence that encodes an amino acid including the triplet sequence, the encoded amino acid or whether it is a start or stop codon.

data_2117.name: Map identifier
data_2117.definition: An identifier of a map of a molecular sequence.

data_2118.name: Person identifier
data_2118.definition: An identifier of a software end-user (typically a person).

data_2119.name: Nucleic acid identifier
data_2119.definition: Name or other identifier of a nucleic acid molecule.

data_2126.name: Translation frame specification
data_2126.definition: Frame for translation of DNA (3 forward and 3 reverse frames relative to a chromosome).

data_2127.name: Genetic code identifier
data_2127.definition: An identifier of a genetic code.

data_2128.name: Genetic code name
data_2128.definition: Informal name for a genetic code, typically an organism name.

data_2129.name: File format name
data_2129.definition: Name of a file format such as HTML, PNG, PDF, EMBL, GenBank and so on.

data_2130.name: Sequence profile type
data_2130.definition: A label (text token) describing a type of sequence profile such as frequency matrix, Gribskov profile, hidden Markov model etc.

data_2131.name: Operating system name
data_2131.definition: Name of a computer operating system such as Linux, PC or Mac.

data_2132.name: Mutation type
data_2132.definition: A type of point or block mutation, including insertion, deletion, change, duplication and moves.

data_2133.name: Logical operator
data_2133.definition: A logical operator such as OR, AND, XOR, and NOT.

data_2134.name: Results sort order
data_2134.definition:
A control of the order of data that is output, for example the order of sequences in an alignment.
Possible options including sorting by score, rank, by increasing P-value (probability, i.e. most statistically significant hits given first) and so on.

data_2135.name: Toggle
data_2135.definition: A simple parameter that is a toggle (boolean value), typically a control for a modal tool.

data_2136.name: Sequence width
data_2136.definition: The width of an output sequence or alignment.

data_2137.name: Gap penalty
data_2137.definition: A penalty for introducing or extending a gap in an alignment.

data_2139.name: Nucleic acid melting temperature
data_2139.definition: A temperature concerning nucleic acid denaturation, typically the temperature at which the two strands of a hybridised or double stranded nucleic acid (DNA or RNA/DNA) molecule separate.

data_2140.name: Concentration
data_2140.definition: The concentration of a chemical compound.

data_2141.name: Window step size
data_2141.definition: Size of the incremental 'step' a sequence window is moved over a sequence.

data_2142.name: EMBOSS graph
data_2142.definition: An image of a graph generated by the EMBOSS suite.

data_2143.name: EMBOSS report
data_2143.definition: An application report generated by the EMBOSS suite.

data_2145.name: Sequence offset
data_2145.definition: An offset for a single-point sequence position.

data_2146.name: Threshold
data_2146.definition: A value that serves as a threshold for a tool (usually to control scoring or output).

data_2147.name: Protein report (transcription factor)
data_2147.definition:
An informative report on a transcription factor protein.
This might include conformational or physicochemical properties, as well as sequence information for transcription factor(s) binding sites.

data_2149.name: Database category name
data_2149.definition: The name of a category of biological or bioinformatics database.

data_2151.name: Color
data_2151.definition: Specification of one or more colors.

data_2152.name: Rendering parameter
data_2152.definition: A parameter that is used to control rendering (drawing) to a device or image.

data_2154.name: Sequence name
data_2154.definition: Any arbitrary name of a molecular sequence.

data_2157.name: Word composition
data_2157.definition: Word composition data for a molecular sequence.

data_2160.name: Fickett testcode plot
data_2160.definition: A plot of Fickett testcode statistic (identifying protein coding regions) in a nucleotide sequences.

data_2161.name: Sequence similarity plot
data_2161.definition:
A plot of sequence similarities identified from word-matching or character comparison.
Use this concept for calculated substitution rates, relative site variability, data on sites with biased properties, highly conserved or very poorly conserved sites, regions, blocks etc.

data_2162.name: Helical wheel
data_2162.definition: An image of peptide sequence sequence looking down the axis of the helix for highlighting amphipathicity and other properties.

data_2163.name: Helical net
data_2163.definition:
An image of peptide sequence sequence in a simple 3,4,3,4 repeating pattern that emulates at a simple level the arrangement of residues around an alpha helix.
Useful for highlighting amphipathicity and other properties.

data_2164.name: Protein sequence properties plot
data_2164.definition: A plot of general physicochemical properties of a protein sequence.

data_2165.name: Protein ionisation curve
data_2165.definition: A plot of pK versus pH for a protein.

data_2166.name: Sequence composition plot
data_2166.definition: A plot of character or word composition / frequency of a molecular sequence.

data_2167.name: Nucleic acid density plot
data_2167.definition: Density plot (of base composition) for a nucleotide sequence.

data_2168.name: Sequence trace image
data_2168.definition: Image of a sequence trace (nucleotide sequence versus probabilities of each of the 4 bases).

data_2169.name: Nucleic acid features (siRNA)
data_2169.definition: A report on siRNA duplexes in mRNA.

data_2173.name: Sequence set (stream)
data_2173.definition:
A collection of multiple molecular sequences and (typically) associated metadata that is intended for sequential processing.
This concept may be used for sequence sets that are expected to be read and processed a single sequence at a time.

data_2174.name: FlyBase secondary identifier
data_2174.definition:
Secondary identifier of an object from the FlyBase database.
Secondary identifier are used to handle entries that were merged with or split from other entries in the database.

data_2176.name: Cardinality
data_2176.definition: The number of a certain thing.

data_2190.name: Sequence checksum
data_2190.definition: A fixed-size datum calculated (by using a hash function) for a molecular sequence, typically for purposes of error detection or indexing.

data_2192.name: Error
data_2192.definition: Data on an error generated by computer system or tool.

data_2193.name: Database entry metadata
data_2193.definition: Basic information on any arbitrary database entry.

data_2201.name: Sequence record full
data_2201.definition: A molecular sequence and comprehensive metadata (such as a feature table), typically corresponding to a full entry from a molecular sequence database.

data_2208.name: Plasmid identifier
data_2208.definition: An identifier of a plasmid in a database.

data_2209.name: Mutation ID
data_2209.definition: A unique identifier of a specific mutation catalogued in a database.

data_2212.name: Mutation annotation (basic)
data_2212.definition: Information describing the mutation itself, the organ site, tissue and type of lesion where the mutation has been identified, description of the patient origin and life-style.

data_2213.name: Mutation annotation (prevalence)
data_2213.definition: An informative report on the prevalence of mutation(s), including data on samples and mutation prevalence (e.g. by tumour type)..

data_2214.name: Mutation annotation (prognostic)
data_2214.definition: An informative report on mutation prognostic data, such as information on patient cohort, the study settings and the results of the study.

data_2215.name: Mutation annotation (functional)
data_2215.definition: An informative report on the functional properties of mutant proteins including transcriptional activities, promotion of cell growth and tumorigenicity, dominant negative effects, capacity to induce apoptosis, cell-cycle arrest or checkpoints in human cells and so on.

data_2216.name: Codon number
data_2216.definition: The number of a codon, for instance, at which a mutation is located.

data_2217.name: Tumor annotation
data_2217.definition: An informative report on a specific tumor including nature and origin of the sample, anatomic site, organ or tissue, tumor type, including morphology and/or histologic type, and so on.

data_2218.name: Server metadata
data_2218.definition: Basic information about a server on the web, such as an SRS server.

data_2219.name: Database field name
data_2219.definition: The name of a field in a database.

data_2220.name: Sequence cluster ID (SYSTERS)
data_2220.definition: Unique identifier of a sequence cluster from the SYSTERS database.

data_2235.name: Raw SCOP domain classification
data_2235.definition:
Raw SCOP domain classification data files.
These are the parsable data files provided by SCOP.

data_2236.name: Raw CATH domain classification
data_2236.definition:
Raw CATH domain classification data files.
These are the parsable data files provided by CATH.

data_2240.name: Heterogen annotation
data_2240.definition: An informative report on the types of small molecules or 'heterogens' (non-protein groups) that are represented in PDB files.

data_2245.name: Sequence set (bootstrapped)
data_2245.definition:
A collection of sequences output from a bootstrapping (resampling) procedure.
Bootstrapping is often performed in phylogenetic analysis.

data_2247.name: Phylogenetic consensus tree
data_2247.definition: A consensus phylogenetic tree derived from comparison of multiple trees.

data_2248.name: Schema
data_2248.definition: A data schema for organising or transforming data of some type.

data_2253.name: Data resource definition name
data_2253.definition: The name of a data type.

data_2254.name: OBO file format name
data_2254.definition: Name of an OBO file format such as OBO-XML, plain and so on.

data_2285.name: Gene ID (MIPS)
data_2285.definition: Identifier for genetic elements in MIPS database.

data_2288.name: Sequence identifier (protein)
data_2288.definition: An identifier of protein sequence(s) or protein sequence database entries.

data_2289.name: Sequence identifier (nucleic acid)
data_2289.definition: An identifier of nucleotide sequence(s) or nucleotide sequence database entries.

data_2290.name: EMBL accession
data_2290.definition: An accession number of an entry from the EMBL sequence database.

data_2291.name: UniProt ID
data_2291.definition: An identifier of a polypeptide in the UniProt database.

data_2292.name: GenBank accession
data_2292.definition: Accession number of an entry from the GenBank sequence database.

data_2293.name: Gramene secondary identifier
data_2293.definition: Secondary (internal) identifier of a Gramene database entry.

data_2294.name: Sequence variation ID
data_2294.definition: An identifier of an entry from a database of molecular sequence variation.

data_2295.name: Gene ID
data_2295.definition: A unique (and typically persistent) identifier of a gene in a database, that is (typically) different to the gene name/symbol.

data_2296.name: Gene name (AceView)
data_2296.definition: Name of an entry (gene) from the AceView genes database.

data_2297.name: Gene ID (ECK)
data_2297.definition: Identifier of an E. coli K-12 gene from EcoGene Database.

data_2298.name: Gene ID (HGNC)
data_2298.definition: Identifier for a gene approved by the HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee.

data_2299.name: Gene name
data_2299.definition: The name of a gene, (typically) assigned by a person and/or according to a naming scheme. It may contain white space characters and is typically more intuitive and readable than a gene symbol. It (typically) may be used to identify similar genes in different species and to derive a gene symbol.

data_2300.name: Gene name (NCBI)
data_2300.definition: Name of an entry (gene) from the NCBI genes database.

data_2301.name: SMILES string
data_2301.definition: A specification of a chemical structure in SMILES format.

data_2302.name: STRING ID
data_2302.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the STRING database of protein-protein interactions.

data_2307.name: Virus annotation
data_2307.definition: An informative report on a specific virus.

data_2308.name: Virus annotation (taxonomy)
data_2308.definition: An informative report on the taxonomy of a specific virus.

data_2309.name: Reaction ID (SABIO-RK)
data_2309.definition: Identifier of a biological reaction from the SABIO-RK reactions database.

data_2313.name: Carbohydrate report
data_2313.definition: A human-readable collection of information about one or more specific carbohydrate 3D structure(s).

data_2314.name: GI number
data_2314.definition:
A series of digits that are assigned consecutively to each sequence record processed by NCBI. The GI number bears no resemblance to the Accession number of the sequence record.
Nucleotide sequence GI number is shown in the VERSION field of the database record. Protein sequence GI number is shown in the CDS/db_xref field of a nucleotide database record, and the VERSION field of a protein database record.

data_2315.name: NCBI version
data_2315.definition:
An identifier assigned to sequence records processed by NCBI, made of the accession number of the database record followed by a dot and a version number.
Nucleotide sequence version contains two letters followed by six digits, a dot, and a version number (or for older nucleotide sequence records, the format is one letter followed by five digits, a dot, and a version number). Protein sequence version contains three letters followed by five digits, a dot, and a version number.

data_2316.name: Cell line name
data_2316.definition: The name of a cell line.

data_2317.name: Cell line name (exact)
data_2317.definition: The name of a cell line.

data_2318.name: Cell line name (truncated)
data_2318.definition: The name of a cell line.

data_2319.name: Cell line name (no punctuation)
data_2319.definition: The name of a cell line.

data_2320.name: Cell line name (assonant)
data_2320.definition: The name of a cell line.

data_2321.name: Enzyme ID
data_2321.definition: A unique, persistent identifier of an enzyme.

data_2325.name: REBASE enzyme number
data_2325.definition: Identifier of an enzyme from the REBASE enzymes database.

data_2326.name: DrugBank ID
data_2326.definition: Unique identifier of a drug from the DrugBank database.

data_2327.name: GI number (protein)
data_2327.definition:
A unique identifier assigned to NCBI protein sequence records.
Nucleotide sequence GI number is shown in the VERSION field of the database record. Protein sequence GI number is shown in the CDS/db_xref field of a nucleotide database record, and the VERSION field of a protein database record.

data_2335.name: Bit score
data_2335.definition:
A score derived from the alignment of two sequences, which is then normalised with respect to the scoring system.
Bit scores are normalised with respect to the scoring system and therefore can be used to compare alignment scores from different searches.

data_2336.name: Translation phase specification
data_2336.definition: Phase for translation of DNA (0, 1 or 2) relative to a fragment of the coding sequence.

data_2337.name: Resource metadata
data_2337.definition:
Data concerning or describing some core computational resource, as distinct from primary data.  This includes metadata on the origin, source, history, ownership or location of some thing.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2338.name: Ontology identifier
data_2338.definition: Any arbitrary identifier of an ontology.

data_2339.name: Ontology concept name
data_2339.definition: The name of a concept in an ontology.

data_2340.name: Genome build identifier
data_2340.definition: An identifier of a build of a particular genome.

data_2342.name: Pathway or network name
data_2342.definition: The name of a biological pathway or network.

data_2343.name: Pathway ID (KEGG)
data_2343.definition: Identifier of a pathway from the KEGG pathway database.

data_2344.name: Pathway ID (NCI-Nature)
data_2344.definition: Identifier of a pathway from the NCI-Nature pathway database.

data_2345.name: Pathway ID (ConsensusPathDB)
data_2345.definition: Identifier of a pathway from the ConsensusPathDB pathway database.

data_2346.name: Sequence cluster ID (UniRef)
data_2346.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the UniRef database.

data_2347.name: Sequence cluster ID (UniRef100)
data_2347.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the UniRef100 database.

data_2348.name: Sequence cluster ID (UniRef90)
data_2348.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the UniRef90 database.

data_2349.name: Sequence cluster ID (UniRef50)
data_2349.definition: Unique identifier of an entry from the UniRef50 database.

data_2353.name: Ontology data
data_2353.definition:
Data concerning or derived from an ontology.

Data concerning a map of molecular sequence(s).

data_2523.name: Phylogenetic data
data_2523.definition:
Data concerning phylogeny, typically of molecular sequences, including reports of information concerning or derived from a phylogenetic tree, or from comparing two or more phylogenetic trees.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2524.name: Protein data
data_2524.definition:
Data concerning one or more protein molecules.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2525.name: Nucleic acid data
data_2525.definition:
Data concerning one or more nucleic acid molecules.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2526.name: Text data
data_2526.definition:
Data concerning, extracted from, or derived from the analysis of a scientific text (or texts) such as a full text article from a scientific journal.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation. It includes concepts that are best described as scientific text or closely concerned with or derived from text.

data_2527.name: Parameter
data_2527.definition: Typically a simple numerical or string value that controls the operation of a tool.

data_2528.name: Molecular data
data_2528.definition:
Data concerning a specific type of molecule.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2529.name: Molecule report
data_2529.definition: An informative report on a specific molecule.

data_2530.name: Organism report
data_2530.definition: A human-readable collection of information about a specific organism.

data_2531.name: Protocol
data_2531.definition: A human-readable collection of information about about how a scientific experiment or analysis was carried out that results in a specific set of data or results used for further analysis or to test a specific hypothesis.

data_2534.name: Sequence attribute
data_2534.definition: An attribute of a molecular sequence, possibly in reference to some other sequence.

data_2535.name: Sequence tag profile
data_2535.definition:
Output from a serial analysis of gene expression (SAGE), massively parallel signature sequencing (MPSS) or sequencing by synthesis (SBS) experiment.  In all cases this is a list of short sequence tags and the number of times it is observed.
This includes tag to gene assignments (tag mapping) of SAGE, MPSS and SBS data. Typically this is the sequencing-based expression profile annotated with gene identifiers.
SAGE, MPSS and SBS experiments are usually performed to study gene expression.  The sequence tags are typically subsequently annotated (after a database search) with the mRNA (and therefore gene) the tag was extracted from.

data_2536.name: Mass spectrometry data
data_2536.definition: Data concerning a mass spectrometry measurement.

data_2537.name: Protein structure raw data
data_2537.definition:
Raw data from experimental methods for determining protein structure.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_2539.name: Alignment data
data_2539.definition:
Data concerning an alignment of two or more molecular sequences, structures or derived data.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.  This includes entities derived from sequences and structures such as motifs and profiles.

data_2540.name: Data index data
data_2540.definition:
Data concerning an index of data.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2713.name: Protein ID (CORUM)
