data_2714.name: CDD PSSM-ID
data_2714.definition: Unique identifier of a position-specific scoring matrix from the CDD database.

data_2715.name: Protein ID (CuticleDB)
data_2715.definition: Unique identifier for a protein from the CuticleDB database.

data_2716.name: DBD ID
data_2716.definition: Identifier of a predicted transcription factor from the DBD database.

data_2717.name: Oligonucleotide probe annotation
data_2717.definition: General annotation on an oligonucleotide probe, or a set of probes.

data_2718.name: Oligonucleotide ID
data_2718.definition: Identifier of an oligonucleotide from a database.

data_2719.name: dbProbe ID
data_2719.definition: Identifier of an oligonucleotide probe from the dbProbe database.

data_2720.name: Dinucleotide property
data_2720.definition: Physicochemical property data for one or more dinucleotides.

data_2721.name: DiProDB ID
data_2721.definition: Identifier of an dinucleotide property from the DiProDB database.

data_2723.name: Protein ID (DisProt)
data_2723.definition: Unique identifier for a protein from the DisProt database.

data_2724.name: Embryo report
data_2724.definition: Annotation on an embryo or concerning embryological development.

data_2725.name: Ensembl transcript ID
data_2725.definition: Unique identifier for a gene transcript from the Ensembl database.

data_2726.name: Inhibitor annotation
data_2726.definition: An informative report on one or more small molecules that are enzyme inhibitors.

data_2727.name: Promoter ID
data_2727.definition: An identifier of a promoter of a gene that is catalogued in a database.

data_2729.name: COGEME EST ID
data_2729.definition: Identifier of an EST sequence from the COGEME database.

data_2730.name: COGEME unisequence ID
data_2730.definition:
Identifier of a unisequence from the COGEME database.
A unisequence is a single sequence assembled from ESTs.

data_2731.name: Protein family ID (GeneFarm)
data_2731.definition: Accession number of an entry (family) from the TIGRFam database.

data_2732.name: Family name
data_2732.definition: The name of a family of organism.

data_2733.name: Genus name (virus)
data_2733.definition: The name of a genus of viruses.

data_2734.name: Family name (virus)
data_2734.definition: The name of a family of viruses.

data_2735.name: Database name (SwissRegulon)
data_2735.definition: The name of a SwissRegulon database.

data_2736.name: Sequence feature ID (SwissRegulon)
data_2736.definition:
A feature identifier as used in the SwissRegulon database.
This can be name of a gene, the ID of a TFBS, or genomic coordinates in form "chr:start..end".

data_2737.name: FIG ID
data_2737.definition:
A unique identifier of gene in the NMPDR database.
A FIG ID consists of four parts: a prefix, genome id, locus type and id number.

data_2738.name: Gene ID (Xenbase)
data_2738.definition: A unique identifier of gene in the Xenbase database.

data_2739.name: Gene ID (Genolist)
data_2739.definition: A unique identifier of gene in the Genolist database.

data_2740.name: Gene name (Genolist)
data_2740.definition: Name of an entry (gene) from the Genolist genes database.

data_2741.name: ABS ID
data_2741.definition: Identifier of an entry (promoter) from the ABS database.

data_2742.name: AraC-XylS ID
data_2742.definition: Identifier of a transcription factor from the AraC-XylS database.

data_2743.name: Gene name (HUGO)
data_2743.definition: Name of an entry (gene) from the HUGO database.

data_2744.name: Locus ID (PseudoCAP)
data_2744.definition: Identifier of a locus from the PseudoCAP database.

data_2745.name: Locus ID (UTR)
data_2745.definition: Identifier of a locus from the UTR database.

data_2746.name: MonosaccharideDB ID
data_2746.definition: Unique identifier of a monosaccharide from the MonosaccharideDB database.

data_2747.name: Database name (CMD)
data_2747.definition: The name of a subdivision of the Collagen Mutation Database (CMD) database.

data_2748.name: Database name (Osteogenesis)
data_2748.definition: The name of a subdivision of the Osteogenesis database.

data_2749.name: Genome identifier
data_2749.definition: An identifier of a particular genome.

data_2751.name: GenomeReviews ID
data_2751.definition: An identifier of a particular genome.

data_2752.name: GlycoMap ID
data_2752.definition: Identifier of an entry from the GlycosciencesDB database.

data_2753.name: Carbohydrate conformational map
data_2753.definition: A conformational energy map of the glycosidic linkages in a carbohydrate molecule.

data_2755.name: Transcription factor name
data_2755.definition: The name of a transcription factor.

data_2756.name: TCID
data_2756.definition: Identifier of a membrane transport proteins from the transport classification database (TCDB).

data_2757.name: Pfam domain name
data_2757.definition: Name of a domain from the Pfam database.

data_2758.name: Pfam clan ID
data_2758.definition: Accession number of a Pfam clan.

data_2759.name: Gene ID (VectorBase)
data_2759.definition: Identifier for a gene from the VectorBase database.

data_2761.name: UTRSite ID
data_2761.definition: Identifier of an entry from the UTRSite database of regulatory motifs in eukaryotic UTRs.

data_2762.name: Sequence signature report
data_2762.definition: An informative report about a specific or conserved pattern in a molecular sequence, such as its context in genes or proteins, its role, origin or method of construction, etc.

data_2763.name: Locus annotation
data_2763.definition: An informative report on a particular locus.

data_2764.name: Protein name (UniProt)
data_2764.definition: Official name of a protein as used in the UniProt database.

data_2765.name: Term ID list
data_2765.definition:
One or more terms from one or more controlled vocabularies which are annotations on an entity.
The concepts are typically provided as a persistent identifier or some other link the source ontologies. Evidence of the validity of the annotation might be included.

data_2766.name: HAMAP ID
data_2766.definition: Name of a protein family from the HAMAP database.

data_2767.name: Identifier with metadata
data_2767.definition: Basic information concerning an identifier of data (typically including the identifier itself).  For example, a gene symbol with information concerning its provenance.

data_2770.name: HIT ID
data_2770.definition: Identifier of an RNA transcript from the H-InvDB database.

data_2771.name: HIX ID
data_2771.definition: A unique identifier of gene cluster in the H-InvDB database.

data_2772.name: HPA antibody id
data_2772.definition: Identifier of a antibody from the HPA database.

data_2773.name: IMGT/HLA ID
data_2773.definition: Identifier of a human major histocompatibility complex (HLA) or other protein from the IMGT/HLA database.

data_2774.name: Gene ID (JCVI)
data_2774.definition: A unique identifier of gene assigned by the J. Craig Venter Institute (JCVI).

data_2775.name: Kinase name
data_2775.definition: The name of a kinase protein.

data_2776.name: ConsensusPathDB entity ID
data_2776.definition: Identifier of a physical entity from the ConsensusPathDB database.

data_2777.name: ConsensusPathDB entity name
data_2777.definition: Name of a physical entity from the ConsensusPathDB database.

data_2778.name: CCAP strain number
data_2778.definition: The number of a strain of algae and protozoa from the CCAP database.

data_2779.name: Stock number
data_2779.definition: An identifier of stock from a catalogue of biological resources.

data_2780.name: Stock number (TAIR)
data_2780.definition: A stock number from The Arabidopsis information resource (TAIR).

data_2781.name: REDIdb ID
data_2781.definition: Identifier of an entry from the RNA editing database (REDIdb).

data_2782.name: SMART domain name
data_2782.definition: Name of a domain from the SMART database.

data_2783.name: Protein family ID (PANTHER)
data_2783.definition: Accession number of an entry (family) from the PANTHER database.

data_2784.name: RNAVirusDB ID
data_2784.definition:
A unique identifier for a virus from the RNAVirusDB database.
Could list (or reference) other taxa here from https://www.phenoscape.org/wiki/Taxonomic_Rank_Vocabulary.

data_2785.name: Virus ID
data_2785.definition: An accession of annotation on a (group of) viruses (catalogued in a database).

data_2786.name: NCBI Genome Project ID
data_2786.definition: An identifier of a genome project assigned by NCBI.

data_2787.name: NCBI genome accession
data_2787.definition: A unique identifier of a whole genome assigned by the NCBI.

data_2788.name: Sequence profile data
data_2788.definition: Data concerning, extracted from, or derived from the analysis of a sequence profile, such as its name, length, technical details about the profile or it's construction, the biological role or annotation, and so on.

data_2789.name: Protein ID (TopDB)
data_2789.definition: Unique identifier for a membrane protein from the TopDB database.

data_2791.name: Reference map name (SWISS-2DPAGE)
data_2791.definition: Name of a reference map gel from the SWISS-2DPAGE database.

data_2792.name: Protein ID (PeroxiBase)
data_2792.definition: Unique identifier for a peroxidase protein from the PeroxiBase database.

data_2793.name: SISYPHUS ID
data_2793.definition: Identifier of an entry from the SISYPHUS database of tertiary structure alignments.

data_2794.name: ORF ID
data_2794.definition: Accession of an open reading frame (catalogued in a database).

data_2795.name: ORF identifier
data_2795.definition: An identifier of an open reading frame.

data_2796.name: Linucs ID
data_2796.definition: Identifier of an entry from the GlycosciencesDB database.

data_2797.name: Protein ID (LGICdb)
data_2797.definition: Unique identifier for a ligand-gated ion channel protein from the LGICdb database.

data_2798.name: MaizeDB ID
data_2798.definition: Identifier of an EST sequence from the MaizeDB database.

data_2799.name: Gene ID (MfunGD)
data_2799.definition: A unique identifier of gene in the MfunGD database.

data_2800.name: Orpha number
data_2800.definition: An identifier of a disease from the Orpha database.

data_2802.name: Protein ID (EcID)
data_2802.definition: Unique identifier for a protein from the EcID database.

data_2803.name: Clone ID (RefSeq)
data_2803.definition: A unique identifier of a cDNA molecule catalogued in the RefSeq database.

data_2804.name: Protein ID (ConoServer)
data_2804.definition: Unique identifier for a cone snail toxin protein from the ConoServer database.

data_2805.name: GeneSNP ID
data_2805.definition: Identifier of a GeneSNP database entry.

data_2832.name: Web portal
data_2832.definition: A web site providing data (web pages) on a common theme to a HTTP client.

data_2835.name: Gene ID (VBASE2)
data_2835.definition: Identifier for a gene from the VBASE2 database.

data_2836.name: DPVweb ID
data_2836.definition: A unique identifier for a virus from the DPVweb database.

data_2837.name: Pathway ID (BioSystems)
data_2837.definition: Identifier of a pathway from the BioSystems pathway database.

data_2849.name: Abstract
data_2849.definition: An abstract of a scientific article.

data_2850.name: Lipid structure
data_2850.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a lipid structure.

data_2851.name: Drug structure
data_2851.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for the (3D) structure of a drug.

data_2852.name: Toxin structure
data_2852.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for the (3D) structure of a toxin.

data_2854.name: Position-specific scoring matrix
data_2854.definition: A simple matrix of numbers, where each value (or column of values) is derived derived from analysis of the corresponding position in a sequence alignment.

data_2855.name: Distance matrix
data_2855.definition: A matrix of distances between molecular entities, where a value (distance) is (typically) derived from comparison of two entities and reflects their similarity.

data_2856.name: Structural distance matrix
data_2856.definition: Distances (values representing similarity) between a group of molecular structures.

data_2858.name: Ontology concept
data_2858.definition:
A concept from a biological ontology.
This includes any fields from the concept definition such as concept name, definition, comments and so on.

data_2865.name: Codon usage bias
data_2865.definition: A numerical measure of differences in the frequency of occurrence of synonymous codons in DNA sequences.

data_2870.name: Radiation hybrid map
data_2870.definition:
A map showing distance between genetic markers estimated by radiation-induced breaks in a chromosome.
The radiation method can break very closely linked markers providing a more detailed map.  Most genetic markers and subsequences may be located to a defined map position and with a more precise estimates of distance than a linkage map.

data_2872.name: ID list
data_2872.definition: A simple list of data identifiers (such as database accessions), possibly with additional basic information on the addressed data.

data_2873.name: Phylogenetic gene frequencies data
data_2873.definition: Gene frequencies data that may be read during phylogenetic tree calculation.

data_2874.name: Sequence set (polymorphic)
data_2874.definition: A set of sub-sequences displaying some type of polymorphism, typically indicating the sequence in which they occur, their position and other metadata.

data_2875.name: DRCAT resource
data_2875.definition: An entry (resource) from the DRCAT bioinformatics resource catalogue.

data_2877.name: Protein complex
data_2877.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a multi-protein complex; two or more polypeptides chains in a stable, functional association with one another.

data_2878.name: Protein structural motif
data_2878.definition: 3D coordinate and associated data for a protein (3D) structural motif; any group of contiguous or non-contiguous amino acid residues but typically those forming a feature with a structural or functional role.

data_2879.name: Lipid report
data_2879.definition: A human-readable collection of information about one or more specific lipid 3D structure(s).

data_2880.name: Secondary structure image
data_2880.definition: Image of one or more molecular secondary structures.

data_2881.name: Secondary structure report
data_2881.definition: An informative report on general information, properties or features of one or more molecular secondary structures.

data_2882.name: DNA features
data_2882.definition: DNA sequence-specific feature annotation (not in a feature table).

data_2883.name: RNA features report
data_2883.definition: Features concerning RNA or regions of DNA that encode an RNA molecule.

data_2884.name: Plot
data_2884.definition: Biological data that has been plotted as a graph of some type, or plotting instructions for rendering such a graph.

data_2886.name: Protein sequence record
data_2886.definition: A protein sequence and associated metadata.

data_2887.name: Nucleic acid sequence record
data_2887.definition: A nucleic acid sequence and associated metadata.

data_2888.name: Protein sequence record (full)
data_2888.definition: A protein sequence and comprehensive metadata (such as a feature table), typically corresponding to a full entry from a molecular sequence database.

data_2889.name: Nucleic acid sequence record (full)
data_2889.definition: A nucleic acid sequence and comprehensive metadata (such as a feature table), typically corresponding to a full entry from a molecular sequence database.

data_2891.name: Biological model accession
data_2891.definition: Accession of a mathematical model, typically an entry from a database.

data_2892.name: Cell type name
data_2892.definition: The name of a type or group of cells.

data_2893.name: Cell type accession
data_2893.definition: Accession of a type or group of cells (catalogued in a database).

data_2894.name: Compound accession
data_2894.definition: Accession of an entry from a database of chemicals.

data_2897.name: Toxin accession
data_2897.definition: Accession of a toxin (catalogued in a database).

data_2898.name: Monosaccharide accession
data_2898.definition: Accession of a monosaccharide (catalogued in a database).

data_2900.name: Carbohydrate accession
data_2900.definition: Accession of an entry from a database of carbohydrates.

data_2901.name: Molecule accession
data_2901.definition: Accession of a specific molecule (catalogued in a database).

data_2902.name: Data resource definition accession
data_2902.definition: Accession of a data definition (catalogued in a database).

data_2903.name: Genome accession
data_2903.definition: An accession of a particular genome (in a database).

data_2904.name: Map accession
data_2904.definition: An accession of a map of a molecular sequence (deposited in a database).

data_2905.name: Lipid accession
data_2905.definition: Accession of an entry from a database of lipids.

data_2906.name: Peptide ID
data_2906.definition: Accession of a peptide deposited in a database.

data_2907.name: Protein accession
data_2907.definition: Accession of a protein deposited in a database.

data_2908.name: Organism accession
data_2908.definition: An accession of annotation on a (group of) organisms (catalogued in a database).

data_2909.name: Organism name
data_2909.definition: The name of an organism (or group of organisms).

data_2910.name: Protein family accession
data_2910.definition: Accession of a protein family (that is deposited in a database).

data_2911.name: Transcription factor accession
data_2911.definition: Accession of an entry from a database of transcription factors or binding sites.

data_2912.name: Strain accession
data_2912.definition: Identifier of a strain of an organism variant, typically a plant, virus or bacterium.

data_2913.name: Virus identifier
data_2913.definition: An accession of annotation on a (group of) viruses (catalogued in a database).

data_2915.name: Gramene identifier
data_2915.definition: Identifier of a Gramene database entry.

data_2916.name: DDBJ accession
data_2916.definition: An identifier of an entry from the DDBJ sequence database.

data_2917.name: ConsensusPathDB identifier
data_2917.definition: An identifier of an entity from the ConsensusPathDB database.

data_2925.name: Sequence data
data_2925.definition:
Data concerning, extracted from, or derived from the analysis of molecular sequence(s).
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2927.name: Codon usage
data_2927.definition:
Data concerning codon usage.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2954.name: Article report
data_2954.definition: Data derived from the analysis of a scientific text such as a full text article from a scientific journal.

data_2955.name: Sequence report
data_2955.definition: An informative report of information about molecular sequence(s), including basic information (metadata), and reports generated from molecular sequence analysis, including positional features and non-positional properties.

data_2956.name: Protein secondary structure
data_2956.definition: Data concerning the properties or features of one or more protein secondary structures.

data_2957.name: Hopp and Woods plot
data_2957.definition: A Hopp and Woods plot of predicted antigenicity of a peptide or protein.

data_2958.name: Nucleic acid melting curve
data_2958.definition: A melting curve of a double-stranded nucleic acid molecule (DNA or DNA/RNA).

data_2959.name: Nucleic acid probability profile
data_2959.definition: A probability profile of a double-stranded nucleic acid molecule (DNA or DNA/RNA).

data_2960.name: Nucleic acid temperature profile
data_2960.definition: A temperature profile of a double-stranded nucleic acid molecule (DNA or DNA/RNA).

data_2961.name: Gene regulatory network report
data_2961.definition: A report typically including a map (diagram) of a gene regulatory network.

data_2965.name: 2D PAGE gel report
data_2965.definition: An informative report on a two-dimensional (2D PAGE) gel.

data_2966.name: Oligonucleotide probe sets annotation
data_2966.definition: General annotation on a set of oligonucleotide probes, such as the gene name with which the probe set is associated and which probes belong to the set.

data_2967.name: Microarray image
data_2967.definition: An image from a microarray experiment which (typically) allows a visualisation of probe hybridisation and gene-expression data.

data_2968.name: Image
data_2968.definition: Data (typically biological or biomedical) that has been rendered into an image, typically for display on screen.

data_2969.name: Sequence image
data_2969.definition: Image of a molecular sequence, possibly with sequence features or properties shown.

data_2970.name: Protein hydropathy data
data_2970.definition: A report on protein properties concerning hydropathy.

data_2973.name: Secondary structure data
data_2973.definition: Data concerning molecular secondary structure data.

data_2974.name: Protein sequence (raw)
data_2974.definition: A raw protein sequence (string of characters).

data_2976.name: Protein sequence
data_2976.definition: One or more protein sequences, possibly with associated annotation.

data_2977.name: Nucleic acid sequence
data_2977.definition: One or more nucleic acid sequences, possibly with associated annotation.

data_2978.name: Reaction data
data_2978.definition:
Data concerning a biochemical reaction, typically data and more general annotation on the kinetics of enzyme-catalysed reaction.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2980.name: Protein classification
data_2980.definition:
An informative report concerning the classification of protein sequences or structures.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2981.name: Sequence motif data
data_2981.definition:
Data concerning specific or conserved pattern in molecular sequences.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2982.name: Sequence profile data
data_2982.definition:
Data concerning models representing a (typically multiple) sequence alignment.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2983.name: Pathway or network data
data_2983.definition: Data concerning a specific biological pathway or network.

data_2984.name: Pathway or network report
data_2984.definition: An informative report concerning or derived from the analysis of a biological pathway or network, such as a map (diagram) or annotation.

data_2985.name: Nucleic acid thermodynamic data
data_2985.definition: A thermodynamic or kinetic property of a nucleic acid molecule.

data_2986.name: Nucleic acid classification
data_2986.definition:
Data concerning the classification of nucleic acid sequences or structures.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_2987.name: Classification report
data_2987.definition:
A report on a classification of molecular sequences, structures or other entities.
This can include an entire classification, components such as classifiers, assignments of entities to a classification and so on.

data_2989.name: Protein features report (key folding sites)
data_2989.definition: key residues involved in protein folding.

data_2991.name: Protein geometry data
data_2991.definition: Geometry data for a protein structure, for example bond lengths, bond angles, torsion angles, chiralities, planaraties etc.

data_2994.name: Phylogenetic character weights
data_2994.definition: Weights for sequence positions or characters in phylogenetic analysis where zero is defined as unweighted.

data_3002.name: Annotation track
data_3002.definition: Annotation of one particular positional feature on a biomolecular (typically genome) sequence, suitable for import and display in a genome browser.

data_3021.name: UniProt accession
data_3021.definition: Accession number of a UniProt (protein sequence) database entry.

data_3022.name: NCBI genetic code ID
data_3022.definition: Identifier of a genetic code in the NCBI list of genetic codes.

data_3025.name: Ontology concept identifier
data_3025.definition: Identifier of a concept in an ontology of biological or bioinformatics concepts and relations.

data_3026.name: GO concept name (biological process)
data_3026.definition: The name of a concept for a biological process from the GO ontology.

data_3027.name: GO concept name (molecular function)
data_3027.definition: The name of a concept for a molecular function from the GO ontology.

data_3028.name: Taxonomy
data_3028.definition:
Data concerning the classification, identification and naming of organisms.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_3029.name: Protein ID (EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ)
data_3029.definition:
EMBL/GENBANK/DDBJ coding feature protein identifier, issued by International collaborators.
This qualifier consists of a stable ID portion (3+5 format with 3 position letters and 5 numbers) plus a version number after the decimal point. When the protein sequence encoded by the CDS changes, only the version number of the /protein_id value is incremented; the stable part of the /protein_id remains unchanged and as a result will permanently be associated with a given protein; this qualifier is valid only on CDS features which translate into a valid protein.

data_3031.name: Core data
data_3031.definition:
A type of data that (typically) corresponds to entries from the primary biological databases and which is (typically) the primary input or output of a tool, i.e. the data the tool processes or generates, as distinct from metadata and identifiers which describe and identify such core data, parameters that control the behaviour of tools, reports of derivative data generated by tools and annotation.
Core data entities typically have a format and may be identified by an accession number.

data_3034.name: Sequence feature identifier
data_3034.definition: Name or other identifier of molecular sequence feature(s).

data_3035.name: Structure identifier
data_3035.definition: An identifier of a molecular tertiary structure, typically an entry from a structure database.

data_3036.name: Matrix identifier
data_3036.definition: An identifier of an array of numerical values, such as a comparison matrix.

data_3085.name: Protein sequence composition
data_3085.definition: A report (typically a table) on character or word composition / frequency of protein sequence(s).

data_3086.name: Nucleic acid sequence composition (report)
data_3086.definition: A report (typically a table) on character or word composition / frequency of nucleic acid sequence(s).

data_3101.name: Protein domain classification node
data_3101.definition: A node from a classification of protein structural domain(s).

data_3102.name: CAS number
data_3102.definition: Unique numerical identifier of chemicals in the scientific literature, as assigned by the Chemical Abstracts Service.

data_3103.name: ATC code
data_3103.definition: Unique identifier of a drug conforming to the Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical (ATC) Classification System, a drug classification system controlled by the WHO Collaborating Centre for Drug Statistics Methodology (WHOCC).

data_3104.name: UNII
data_3104.definition: A unique, unambiguous, alphanumeric identifier of a chemical substance as catalogued by the Substance Registration System of the Food and Drug Administration (FDA).

data_3105.name: Geotemporal metadata
data_3105.definition: Basic information concerning geographical location or time.

data_3106.name: System metadata
data_3106.definition: Metadata concerning the software, hardware or other aspects of a computer system.

data_3107.name: Sequence feature name
data_3107.definition: A name of a sequence feature, e.g. the name of a feature to be displayed to an end-user.

data_3108.name: Experimental measurement
data_3108.definition:
Raw data such as measurements or other results from laboratory experiments, as generated from laboratory hardware.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types. It is primarily intended to help navigation of EDAM and would not typically be used for annotation.

data_3110.name: Raw microarray data
data_3110.definition:
Raw data (typically MIAME-compliant) for hybridisations from a microarray experiment.
Such data as found in Affymetrix CEL or GPR files.

data_3111.name: Processed microarray data
data_3111.definition:
Data generated from processing and analysis of probe set data from a microarray experiment.
Such data as found in Affymetrix .CHP files or data from other software such as RMA or dChip.

data_3112.name: Gene expression matrix
data_3112.definition:
The final processed (normalised) data for a set of hybridisations in a microarray experiment.
This combines data from all hybridisations.

data_3113.name: Sample annotation
data_3113.definition:
Annotation on a biological sample, for example experimental factors and their values.
This might include compound and dose in a dose response experiment.

data_3115.name: Microarray metadata
data_3115.definition:
Annotation on the array itself used in a microarray experiment.
This might include gene identifiers, genomic coordinates, probe oligonucleotide sequences etc.

data_3116.name: Microarray protocol annotation
data_3116.definition:
Annotation on laboratory and/or data processing protocols used in an microarray experiment.
This might describe e.g. the normalisation methods used to process the raw data.

data_3117.name: Microarray hybridisation data
data_3117.definition: Data concerning the hybridisations measured during a microarray experiment.

data_3119.name: Sequence features (compositionally-biased regions)
data_3119.definition: A report of regions in a molecular sequence that are biased to certain characters.

data_3122.name: Nucleic acid features (difference and change)
data_3122.definition: A report on features in a nucleic acid sequence that indicate changes to or differences between sequences.

data_3128.name: Nucleic acid structure report
data_3128.definition: A human-readable collection of information about regions within a nucleic acid sequence which form secondary or tertiary (3D) structures.

data_3129.name: Protein features report (repeats)
data_3129.definition: short repetitive subsequences (repeat sequences) in a protein sequence.

data_3130.name: Sequence motif matches (protein)
data_3130.definition: Report on the location of matches to profiles, motifs (conserved or functional patterns) or other signatures in one or more protein sequences.

data_3131.name: Sequence motif matches (nucleic acid)
data_3131.definition: Report on the location of matches to profiles, motifs (conserved or functional patterns) or other signatures in one or more nucleic acid sequences.

data_3132.name: Nucleic acid features (d-loop)
data_3132.definition:
A report on displacement loops in a mitochondrial DNA sequence.
A displacement loop is a region of mitochondrial DNA in which one of the strands is displaced by an RNA molecule.

data_3133.name: Nucleic acid features (stem loop)
data_3133.definition:
A report on stem loops in a DNA sequence.
A stem loop is a hairpin structure; a double-helical structure formed when two complementary regions of a single strand of RNA or DNA molecule form base-pairs.

data_3134.name: Gene transcript report
data_3134.definition:
An informative report on features of a messenger RNA (mRNA) molecules including precursor RNA, primary (unprocessed) transcript and fully processed molecules. This includes reports on a specific gene transcript, clone or EST.
This includes 5'untranslated region (5'UTR), coding sequences (CDS), exons, intervening sequences (intron) and 3'untranslated regions (3'UTR).

data_3137.name: Non-coding RNA
data_3137.definition: features of non-coding or functional RNA molecules, including tRNA and rRNA.

data_3138.name: Transcriptional features (report)
data_3138.definition:
Features concerning transcription of DNA into RNA including the regulation of transcription.
This includes promoters, CAAT signals, TATA signals, -35 signals, -10 signals, GC signals, primer binding sites for initiation of transcription or reverse transcription, enhancer, attenuator, terminators and ribosome binding sites.

data_3140.name: Nucleic acid features (immunoglobulin gene structure)
data_3140.definition: A report on predicted or actual immunoglobulin gene structure including constant, switch and variable regions and diversity, joining and variable segments.

data_3141.name: SCOP class
data_3141.definition: Information on a 'class' node from the SCOP database.

data_3142.name: SCOP fold
data_3142.definition: Information on a 'fold' node from the SCOP database.

data_3143.name: SCOP superfamily
data_3143.definition: Information on a 'superfamily' node from the SCOP database.

data_3144.name: SCOP family
data_3144.definition: Information on a 'family' node from the SCOP database.

data_3145.name: SCOP protein
data_3145.definition: Information on a 'protein' node from the SCOP database.

data_3146.name: SCOP species
data_3146.definition: Information on a 'species' node from the SCOP database.

data_3148.name: Gene family report
data_3148.definition:
A human-readable collection of information about a particular family of genes, typically a set of genes with similar sequence that originate from duplication of a common ancestor gene, or any other classification of nucleic acid sequences or structures that reflects gene structure.
This includes reports on on gene homologues between species.

data_3154.name: Protein alignment
data_3154.definition: An alignment of protein sequences and/or structures.

data_3165.name: NGS experiment
data_3165.definition: sequencing experiment, including samples, sampling, preparation, sequencing, and analysis.

data_3181.name: Sequence assembly report
data_3181.definition:
An informative report about a DNA sequence assembly.
This might include an overall quality assement of the assembly and summary statistics including counts, average length and number of bases for reads, matches and non-matches, contigs, reads in pairs etc.

data_3210.name: Genome index
data_3210.definition:
An index of a genome sequence.
Many sequence alignment tasks involving many or very large sequences rely on a precomputed index of the sequence to accelerate the alignment.

data_3231.name: GWAS report
data_3231.definition: Report concerning genome-wide association study experiments.

data_3236.name: Cytoband position
data_3236.definition:
The position of a cytogenetic band in a genome.
Information might include start and end position in a chromosome sequence, chromosome identifier, name of band and so on.

data_3241.name: Kinetic model
data_3241.definition: Mathematical model of a network, that contains biochemical kinetics.

data_3264.name: COSMIC ID
data_3264.definition: Identifier of a COSMIC database entry.

data_3265.name: HGMD ID
data_3265.definition: Identifier of a HGMD database entry.

data_3268.name: Sequence feature type
data_3268.definition: A label (text token) describing a type of sequence feature such as gene, transcript, cds, exon, repeat, simple, misc, variation, somatic variation, structural variation, somatic structural variation, constrained or regulatory.

data_3269.name: Gene homology (report)
data_3269.definition: An informative report on gene homologues between species.

data_3270.name: Ensembl gene tree ID
data_3270.definition: Unique identifier for a gene tree from the Ensembl database.

data_3271.name: Gene tree
data_3271.definition: A phylogenetic tree that is an estimate of the character's phylogeny.

data_3272.name: Species tree
data_3272.definition: A phylogenetic tree that reflects phylogeny of the taxa from which the characters (used in calculating the tree) were sampled.

data_3273.name: Sample ID
data_3273.definition: Name or other identifier of an entry from a biosample database.

data_3274.name: MGI accession
data_3274.definition: Identifier of an object from the MGI database.

data_3354.name: Transition matrix
data_3354.definition:
A HMM transition matrix contains the probabilities of switching from one HMM state to another.
Consider for example an HMM with two states (AT-rich and GC-rich).  The transition matrix will hold the probabilities of switching from the AT-rich to the GC-rich state, and vica versa.

data_3355.name: Emission matrix
data_3355.definition:
A HMM emission matrix holds the probabilities of choosing the four nucleotides (A, C, G and T) in each of the states of a HMM.
Consider for example an HMM with two states (AT-rich and GC-rich).  The emission matrix holds the probabilities of choosing each of the four nucleotides (A, C, G and T) in the AT-rich state and in the GC-rich state.

data_3356.name: Hidden Markov model
data_3356.definition: A statistical Markov model of a system which is assumed to be a Markov process with unobserved (hidden) states.

data_3358.name: Format identifier
data_3358.definition: An identifier of a data format.

data_3424.name: Raw image
data_3424.definition: Raw biological or biomedical image generated by some experimental technique.

data_3425.name: Carbohydrate property
data_3425.definition: Data concerning the intrinsic physical (e.g. structural) or chemical properties of one, more or all carbohydrates.

data_3428.name: Simulation experiment report
data_3428.definition: biological computational model experiments (simulation), for example the minimum information required in order to permit its correct interpretation and reproduction.

data_3442.name: MRI image
data_3442.definition: An imaging technique that uses magnetic fields and radiowaves to form images, typically to investigate the anatomy and physiology of the human body.

data_3449.name: Cell migration track image
data_3449.definition: An image from a cell migration track assay.

data_3451.name: Rate of association
data_3451.definition: Rate of association of a protein with another protein or some other molecule.

data_3479.name: Gene order
data_3479.definition:
Multiple gene identifiers in a specific order.
Such data are often used for genome rearrangement tools and phylogenetic tree labeling.

data_3483.name: Spectrum
data_3483.definition: The spectrum of frequencies of electromagnetic radiation emitted from a molecule as a result of some spectroscopy experiment.

data_3488.name: NMR spectrum
data_3488.definition: Spectral information for a molecule from a nuclear magnetic resonance experiment.

data_3490.name: Chemical structure sketch
data_3490.definition:
A sketch of a small molecule made with some specialised drawing package.
Chemical structure sketches are used for presentational purposes but also as inputs to various analysis software.

data_3492.name: Nucleic acid signature
data_3492.definition: An informative report about a specific or conserved nucleic acid sequence pattern.

data_3498.name: Sequence variations
data_3498.definition:
Data on gene sequence variations resulting large-scale genotyping and DNA sequencing projects.
Variations are stored along with a reference genome.

data_3505.name: Bibliography
data_3505.definition: A list of publications such as scientic papers or books.

data_3509.name: Ontology mapping
data_3509.definition: A mapping of supplied textual terms or phrases to ontology concepts (URIs).

data_3546.name: Image metadata
data_3546.definition:
Any data concerning a specific biological or biomedical image.
This can include basic provenance and technical information about the image, scientific annotation and so on.

data_3558.name: Clinical trial report
data_3558.definition: A human-readable collection of information concerning a clinical trial.

data_3568.name: Gene Expression Atlas Experiment ID
data_3568.definition: Accession number of an entry from the Gene Expression Atlas.

data_3667.name: Disease identifier
data_3667.definition: Identifier of an entry from a database of disease.

data_3669.name: Training material
data_3669.definition: Some material that is used for educational (training) purposes.

data_3670.name: Online course
data_3670.definition: A training course available for use on the Web.

data_3671.name: Text
data_3671.definition: Any free or plain text, typically for human consumption and in English. Can instantiate also as a textual search query.

data_3716.name: Biosafety report
data_3716.definition: A human-readable collection of information concerning biosafety data.

data_3717.name: Isolation report
data_3717.definition: A report about any kind of isolation of biological material.

data_3718.name: Pathogenicity report
data_3718.definition: Information about the ability of an organism to cause disease in a corresponding host.

data_3719.name: Biosafety classification
data_3719.definition: Information about the biosafety classification of an organism according to corresponding law.

data_3720.name: Geographic location
data_3720.definition: A report about localisation of the isolaton of biological material e.g. country or coordinates.

data_3721.name: Isolation source
data_3721.definition: A report about any kind of isolation source of biological material e.g. blood, water, soil.

data_3722.name: Physiology parameter
data_3722.definition: Experimentally determined parameter of the physiology of an organism, e.g. substrate spectrum.

data_3723.name: Morphology parameter
data_3723.definition: Experimentally determined parameter of the morphology of an organism, e.g. size & shape.

data_3724.name: Cultivation parameter
data_3724.definition: Experimental determined parameter for the cultivation of an organism.

data_3732.name: Sequencing metadata name
data_3732.definition: Data concerning a sequencing experiment, that may be specified as an input to some tool.

data_3733.name: Flow cell identifier
data_3733.definition:
An identifier of a flow cell of a sequencing machine.
A flow cell is used to immobilise, amplify and sequence millions of molecules at once.  In Illumina machines, a flowcell is composed of  8 "lanes" which allows 8 experiments in a single analysis.

data_3734.name: Lane identifier
data_3734.definition: An identifier of a lane within a flow cell of a sequencing machine, within which millions of sequences are immobilised, amplified and sequenced.

data_3735.name: Run number
data_3735.definition: A number corresponding to the number of an analysis performed by a sequencing machine.  For example, if it's the 13th analysis, the run is 13.

data_3736.name: Ecological data
data_3736.definition:
Data concerning ecology; for example measurements and reports from the study of interactions among organisms and their environment.
This is a broad data type and is used a placeholder for other, more specific types.

data_3737.name: Alpha diversity data
data_3737.definition: The mean species diversity in sites or habitats at a local scale.

data_3738.name: Beta diversity data
data_3738.definition: The ratio between regional and local species diversity.

data_3739.name: Gamma diversity data
data_3739.definition: The total species diversity in a landscape.

data_3743.name: Ordination plot
data_3743.definition: A plot in which community data (e.g. species abundance data) is summarised.  Similar species and samples are plotted close together, and dissimilar species and samples are plotted placed far apart.

data_3753.name: Over-representation data
data_3753.definition: A ranked list of categories (usually ontology concepts), each associated with a statistical metric of over-/under-representation within the studied data.

data_3754.name: GO-term enrichment data
data_3754.definition: A ranked list of Gene Ontology concepts, each associated with a p-value, concerning or derived from the analysis of e.g. a set of genes or proteins.

data_3756.name: Localisation score
data_3756.definition: Score for localization of one or more post-translational modifications in peptide sequence measured by mass spectrometry.

data_3757.name: Unimod ID
data_3757.definition: Identifier of a protein modification catalogued in the Unimod database.

data_3759.name: ProteomeXchange ID
data_3759.definition: Identifier for mass spectrometry proteomics data in the proteomexchange.org repository.

data_3768.name: Clustered expression profiles
data_3768.definition: Groupings of expression profiles according to a clustering algorithm.

data_3769.name: BRENDA ontology concept ID
data_3769.definition: An identifier of a concept from the BRENDA ontology.

data_3779.name: Annotated text
data_3779.definition: A text (such as a scientific article), annotated with notes, data and metadata, such as recognised entities, concepts, and their relations.

data_3786.name: Query script
data_3786.definition: A structured query, in form of a script, that defines a database search task.

data_3805.name: 3D EM Map
data_3805.definition: Structural 3D model (volume map) from electron microscopy.

data_3806.name: 3D EM Mask
data_3806.definition: Annotation on a structural 3D EM Map from electron microscopy. This might include one or several locations in the map of the known features of a particular macromolecule.

data_3807.name: EM Movie
data_3807.definition: Raw DDD movie acquisition from electron microscopy.

data_3808.name: EM Micrograph
data_3808.definition: Raw acquistion from electron microscopy or average of an aligned DDD movie.

data_3842.name: Molecular simulation data
data_3842.definition:
Data coming from molecular simulations, computer "experiments" on model molecules.
Typically formed by two separated but indivisible pieces of information: topology data (static) and trajectory data (dynamic).

data_3856.name: RNA central ID
data_3856.definition:
Identifier of an entry from the RNA central database of annotated human miRNAs.
There are canonical and taxon-specific forms of RNAcentral ID. Canonical form e.g. urs_9or10digits identifies an RNA sequence (within the RNA central database) which may appear in multiple sequences. Taxon-specific form identifies a sequence in the specific taxon (e.g. urs_9or10digits_taxonID).

data_3861.name: Electronic health record
data_3861.definition: A human-readable systematic collection of patient (or population) health information in a digital format.

data_3869.name: Simulation
data_3869.definition: Data coming from molecular simulations, computer "experiments" on model molecules. Tipically formed by two separated but indivisible pieces of information: topology data (static) and trajectory data (dynamic).

data_3870.name: Trajectory data
data_3870.definition: Dynamic information of a structure molecular system coming from a molecular simulation: XYZ 3D coordinates (sometimes with their associated velocities) for every atom along time.

data_3871.name: Forcefield parameters
data_3871.definition: Force field parameters: charges, masses, radii, bond lengths, bond dihedrals, etc. define the structural molecular system, and are essential for the proper description and simulation of a molecular system.

data_3872.name: Topology data
data_3872.definition: Static information of a structure molecular system that is needed for a molecular simulation: the list of atoms, their non-bonded parameters for Van der Waals and electrostatic interactions, and the complete connectivity in terms of bonds, angles and dihedrals.

data_3905.name: Histogram
data_3905.definition: Visualization of distribution of quantitative data, e.g. expression data, by histograms, violin plots and density plots.

data_3914.name: Quality control report
data_3914.definition: A human-readable collection of information about about how a scientific experiment or analysis was carried out that results in a specific set of data or results used for further analysis or to test a specific hypothesis.

data_3917.name: Count matrix
data_3917.definition: A table of unnormalized values representing summarised read counts per genomic region (e.g. gene, transcript, peak).

data_3932.name: Q-value
data_3932.definition:
A score derived from the P-value to ensure correction for multiple tests. The Q-value provides an estimate of the positive False Discovery Rate (pFDR), i.e. the rate of false positives among all the cases reported positive: pFDR = FP / (FP + TP).
Q-values are widely used in high-throughput data analysis (e.g. detection of differentially expressed genes from transcriptome data).

data_3949.name: Profile HMM
data_3949.definition: A profile HMM is a variant of a Hidden Markov model that is derived specifically from a set of (aligned) biological sequences. Profile HMMs provide the basis for a position-specific scoring system, which can be used to align sequences and search databases for related sequences.

data_3952.name: Pathway ID (WikiPathways)
data_3952.definition: Identifier of a pathway from the WikiPathways pathway database.

data_3953.name: Pathway overrepresentation data
data_3953.definition: A ranked list of pathways, each associated with z-score, p-value or similar, concerning or derived from the analysis of e.g. a set of genes or proteins.

format_1196.name: SMILES
format_1196.definition: Chemical structure specified in Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry System (SMILES) line notation.

format_1197.name: InChI
format_1197.definition: Chemical structure specified in IUPAC International Chemical Identifier (InChI) line notation.

format_1198.name: mf
format_1198.definition:
Chemical structure specified by Molecular Formula (MF), including a count of each element in a compound.
The general MF query format consists of a series of valid atomic symbols, with an optional number or range.

format_1199.name: InChIKey
format_1199.definition:
The InChIKey (hashed InChI) is a fixed length (25 character) condensed digital representation of an InChI chemical structure specification. It uniquely identifies a chemical compound.
An InChIKey identifier is not human- nor machine-readable but is more suitable for web searches than an InChI chemical structure specification.

format_1200.name: smarts
format_1200.definition: SMILES ARbitrary Target Specification (SMARTS) format for chemical structure specification, which is a subset of the SMILES line notation.

format_1206.name: unambiguous pure
format_1206.definition: Alphabet for a molecular sequence with possible unknown positions but without ambiguity or non-sequence characters.

format_1207.name: nucleotide
format_1207.definition:
Alphabet for a nucleotide sequence with possible ambiguity, unknown positions and non-sequence characters.
Non-sequence characters may be used for example for gaps.

format_1208.name: protein
format_1208.definition:
Alphabet for a protein sequence with possible ambiguity, unknown positions and non-sequence characters.
Non-sequence characters may be used for gaps and translation stop.

format_1209.name: consensus
format_1209.definition: Alphabet for the consensus of two or more molecular sequences.

format_1210.name: pure nucleotide
format_1210.definition: Alphabet for a nucleotide sequence with possible ambiguity and unknown positions but without non-sequence characters.

format_1211.name: unambiguous pure nucleotide
format_1211.definition: Alphabet for a nucleotide sequence (characters ACGTU only) with possible unknown positions but without ambiguity or non-sequence characters .

format_1212.name: dna
format_1212.definition: Alphabet for a DNA sequence with possible ambiguity, unknown positions and non-sequence characters.

format_1213.name: rna
format_1213.definition: Alphabet for an RNA sequence with possible ambiguity, unknown positions and non-sequence characters.

format_1214.name: unambiguous pure dna
format_1214.definition: Alphabet for a DNA sequence (characters ACGT only) with possible unknown positions but without ambiguity or non-sequence characters.

format_1215.name: pure dna
format_1215.definition: Alphabet for a DNA sequence with possible ambiguity and unknown positions but without non-sequence characters.

format_1216.name: unambiguous pure rna sequence
format_1216.definition: Alphabet for an RNA sequence (characters ACGU only) with possible unknown positions but without ambiguity or non-sequence characters.

format_1217.name: pure rna
format_1217.definition: Alphabet for an RNA sequence with possible ambiguity and unknown positions but without non-sequence characters.

format_1218.name: unambiguous pure protein
format_1218.definition: Alphabet for any protein sequence with possible unknown positions but without ambiguity or non-sequence characters.

format_1219.name: pure protein
format_1219.definition: Alphabet for any protein sequence with possible ambiguity and unknown positions but without non-sequence characters.

format_1228.name: UniGene entry format
format_1228.definition:
Format of an entry from UniGene.
A UniGene entry includes a set of transcript sequences assigned to the same transcription locus (gene or expressed pseudogene), with information on protein similarities, gene expression, cDNA clone reagents, and genomic location.

format_1247.name: COG sequence cluster format
format_1247.definition: Format of an entry from the COG database of clusters of (related) protein sequences.

format_1248.name: EMBL feature location
format_1248.definition: Format for sequence positions (feature location) as used in DDBJ/EMBL/GenBank database.

format_1295.name: quicktandem
format_1295.definition: Report format for tandem repeats in a nucleotide sequence (format generated by the Sanger Centre quicktandem program).

format_1296.name: Sanger inverted repeats
format_1296.definition: Report format for inverted repeats in a nucleotide sequence (format generated by the Sanger Centre inverted program).

format_1297.name: EMBOSS repeat
format_1297.definition: Report format for tandem repeats in a sequence (an EMBOSS report format).

format_1316.name: est2genome format
format_1316.definition: Format of a report on exon-intron structure generated by EMBOSS est2genome.

format_1318.name: restrict format
format_1318.definition: Report format for restriction enzyme recognition sites used by EMBOSS restrict program.

format_1319.name: restover format
format_1319.definition: Report format for restriction enzyme recognition sites used by EMBOSS restover program.

format_1320.name: REBASE restriction sites
format_1320.definition: Report format for restriction enzyme recognition sites used by REBASE database.

format_1332.name: FASTA search results format
format_1332.definition:
Format of results of a sequence database search using FASTA.
This includes (typically) score data, alignment data and a histogram (of observed and expected distribution of E values.)

format_1333.name: BLAST results
format_1333.definition:
Format of results of a sequence database search using some variant of BLAST.
This includes score data, alignment data and summary table.

format_1334.name: mspcrunch
format_1334.definition: Format of results of a sequence database search using some variant of MSPCrunch.

format_1335.name: Smith-Waterman format
format_1335.definition: Format of results of a sequence database search using some variant of Smith Waterman.

format_1336.name: dhf
format_1336.definition:
Format of EMBASSY domain hits file (DHF) of hits (sequences) with domain classification information.
The hits are relatives to a SCOP or CATH family and are found from a search of a sequence database.

format_1337.name: lhf
format_1337.definition:
Format of EMBASSY ligand hits file (LHF) of database hits (sequences) with ligand classification information.
The hits are putative ligand-binding sequences and are found from a search of a sequence database.

format_1341.name: InterPro hits format
format_1341.definition: Results format for searches of the InterPro database.

format_1342.name: InterPro protein view report format
format_1342.definition:
Format of results of a search of the InterPro database showing matches of query protein sequence(s) to InterPro entries.
The report includes a classification of regions in a query protein sequence which are assigned to a known InterPro protein family or group.

format_1343.name: InterPro match table format
format_1343.definition:
Format of results of a search of the InterPro database showing matches between protein sequence(s) and signatures for an InterPro entry.
The table presents matches between query proteins (rows) and signature methods (columns) for this entry. Alternatively the sequence(s) might be from from the InterPro entry itself. The match position in the protein sequence and match status (true positive, false positive etc) are indicated.

format_1351.name: HMMER emission and transition
format_1351.definition: Format of a report from the HMMER package on the emission and transition counts of a hidden Markov model.

format_1356.name: prosite-pattern
format_1356.definition: Format of a regular expression pattern from the Prosite database.

format_1357.name: EMBOSS sequence pattern
format_1357.definition: Format of an EMBOSS sequence pattern.

format_1360.name: meme-motif
format_1360.definition: A motif in the format generated by the MEME program.

format_1366.name: prosite-profile
format_1366.definition: Sequence profile (sequence classifier) format used in the PROSITE database.

format_1367.name: JASPAR format
format_1367.definition: A profile (sequence classifier) in the format used in the JASPAR database.

format_1369.name: MEME background Markov model
format_1369.definition: Format of the model of random sequences used by MEME.

format_1370.name: HMMER format
format_1370.definition: Format of a hidden Markov model representation used by the HMMER package.

format_1391.name: HMMER-aln
format_1391.definition: FASTA-style format for multiple sequences aligned by HMMER package to an HMM.

format_1392.name: DIALIGN format
format_1392.definition: Format of multiple sequences aligned by DIALIGN package.

format_1393.name: daf
format_1393.definition:
EMBASSY 'domain alignment file' (DAF) format, containing a sequence alignment of protein domains belonging to the same SCOP or CATH family.
The format is clustal-like and includes annotation of domain family classification information.

format_1419.name: Sequence-MEME profile alignment
format_1419.definition: Format for alignment of molecular sequences to MEME profiles (position-dependent scoring matrices) as generated by the MAST tool from the MEME package.

format_1421.name: HMMER profile alignment (sequences versus HMMs)
format_1421.definition: Format used by the HMMER package for an alignment of a sequence against a hidden Markov model database.

format_1422.name: HMMER profile alignment (HMM versus sequences)
format_1422.definition: Format used by the HMMER package for of an alignment of a hidden Markov model against a sequence database.

format_1423.name: Phylip distance matrix
format_1423.definition:
Format of PHYLIP phylogenetic distance matrix data.
Data Type must include the distance matrix, probably as pairs of sequence identifiers with a distance (integer or float).

format_1424.name: ClustalW dendrogram
format_1424.definition: Dendrogram (tree file) format generated by ClustalW.

format_1425.name: Phylip tree raw
format_1425.definition: Raw data file format used by Phylip from which a phylogenetic tree is directly generated or plotted.

format_1430.name: Phylip continuous quantitative characters
format_1430.definition: PHYLIP file format for continuous quantitative character data.

format_1432.name: Phylip character frequencies format
format_1432.definition: PHYLIP file format for phylogenetics character frequency data.

format_1433.name: Phylip discrete states format
format_1433.definition: Format of PHYLIP discrete states data.

format_1435.name: Phylip tree format
format_1435.definition: Phylogenetic tree data format used by the PHYLIP program.

format_1436.name: TreeBASE format
format_1436.definition: The format of an entry from the TreeBASE database of phylogenetic data.

format_1437.name: TreeFam format
format_1437.definition: The format of an entry from the TreeFam database of phylogenetic data.

format_1445.name: Phylip tree distance format
format_1445.definition: Format for distances, such as Branch Score distance, between two or more phylogenetic trees as used by the Phylip package.

format_1454.name: dssp
format_1454.definition:
Format of an entry from the DSSP database (Dictionary of Secondary Structure in Proteins).
The DSSP database is built using the DSSP application which defines secondary structure, geometrical features and solvent exposure of proteins, given atomic coordinates in PDB format.

format_1455.name: hssp
format_1455.definition: Entry format of the HSSP database (Homology-derived Secondary Structure in Proteins).

format_1457.name: Dot-bracket format
format_1457.definition: Format of RNA secondary structure in dot-bracket notation, originally generated by the Vienna RNA package/server.

format_1458.name: Vienna local RNA secondary structure format
format_1458.definition: Format of local RNA secondary structure components with free energy values, generated by the Vienna RNA package/server.

format_1475.name: PDB database entry format
format_1475.definition: Format of an entry (or part of an entry) from the PDB database.

format_1476.name: PDB
format_1476.definition: Entry format of PDB database in PDB format.

format_1477.name: mmCIF
format_1477.definition: Entry format of PDB database in mmCIF format.

format_1478.name: PDBML
format_1478.definition: Entry format of PDB database in PDBML (XML) format.

format_1500.name: Domainatrix 3D-1D scoring matrix format
format_1500.definition: Format of a matrix of 3D-1D scores used by the EMBOSS Domainatrix applications.

format_1504.name: aaindex
format_1504.definition: Amino acid index format used by the AAindex database.

format_1511.name: IntEnz enzyme report format
format_1511.definition:
Format of an entry from IntEnz (The Integrated Relational Enzyme Database).
IntEnz is the master copy of the Enzyme Nomenclature, the recommendations of the NC-IUBMB on the Nomenclature and Classification of Enzyme-Catalysed Reactions.

format_1512.name: BRENDA enzyme report format
format_1512.definition: Format of an entry from the BRENDA enzyme database.

format_1513.name: KEGG REACTION enzyme report format
format_1513.definition: Format of an entry from the KEGG REACTION database of biochemical reactions.

format_1514.name: KEGG ENZYME enzyme report format
format_1514.definition: Format of an entry from the KEGG ENZYME database.

format_1515.name: REBASE proto enzyme report format
format_1515.definition: Format of an entry from the proto section of the REBASE enzyme database.

format_1516.name: REBASE withrefm enzyme report format
format_1516.definition: Format of an entry from the withrefm section of the REBASE enzyme database.

format_1551.name: Pcons report format
format_1551.definition:
Format of output of the Pcons Model Quality Assessment Program (MQAP).
Pcons ranks protein models by assessing their quality based on the occurrence of recurring common three-dimensional structural patterns. Pcons returns a score reflecting the overall global quality and a score for each individual residue in the protein reflecting the local residue quality.

format_1552.name: ProQ report format
format_1552.definition:
Format of output of the ProQ protein model quality predictor.
ProQ is a neural network-based predictor that predicts the quality of a protein model based on the number of structural features.

format_1563.name: SMART domain assignment report format
format_1563.definition:
Format of SMART domain assignment data.
The SMART output file includes data on genetically mobile domains / analysis of domain architectures, including phyletic distributions, functional class, tertiary structures and functionally important residues.

format_1568.name: BIND entry format
format_1568.definition: Entry format for the BIND database of protein interaction.

format_1569.name: IntAct entry format
format_1569.definition: Entry format for the IntAct database of protein interaction.

format_1570.name: InterPro entry format
format_1570.definition:
Entry format for the InterPro database of protein signatures (sequence classifiers) and classified sequences.
This includes signature metadata, sequence references and a reference to the signature itself. There is normally a header (entry accession numbers and name), abstract, taxonomy information, example proteins etc. Each entry also includes a match list which give a number of different views of the signature matches for the sequences in each InterPro entry.

format_1571.name: InterPro entry abstract format
format_1571.definition:
Entry format for the textual abstract of signatures in an InterPro entry and its protein matches.
References are included and a functional inference is made where possible.

format_1572.name: Gene3D entry format
format_1572.definition: Entry format for the Gene3D protein secondary database.

format_1573.name: PIRSF entry format
format_1573.definition: Entry format for the PIRSF protein secondary database.

format_1574.name: PRINTS entry format
format_1574.definition: Entry format for the PRINTS protein secondary database.

format_1575.name: Panther Families and HMMs entry format
format_1575.definition: Entry format for the Panther library of protein families and subfamilies.

format_1576.name: Pfam entry format
format_1576.definition: Entry format for the Pfam protein secondary database.

format_1577.name: SMART entry format
format_1577.definition: Entry format for the SMART protein secondary database.

format_1578.definition: Entry format for the Superfamily protein secondary database.

format_1579.name: TIGRFam entry format
format_1579.definition: Entry format for the TIGRFam protein secondary database.

format_1580.name: ProDom entry format
format_1580.definition: Entry format for the ProDom protein domain classification database.

format_1581.name: FSSP entry format
format_1581.definition: Entry format for the FSSP database.

format_1610.definition: Entry format of KEGG GENES genome database.

format_1619.definition: Entry format of the TIGR genome database.

format_1623.definition: Format of an entry from the OMIM database of genotypes and phenotypes.

format_1624.definition: Format of a record from the HGVbase database of genotypes and phenotypes.

format_1625.name: HIVDB entry format
format_1625.definition: Format of a record from the HIVDB database of genotypes and phenotypes.

format_1626.definition: Format of an entry from the KEGG DISEASE database.

format_1644.name: CHP
format_1644.definition: Format of Affymetrix data file of information about (normalised) expression levels of the individual probes.

format_1645.name: EMDB entry format
format_1645.definition: Format of an entry from the Electron Microscopy DataBase (EMDB).

format_1647.name: KEGG PATHWAY entry format
format_1647.definition: The format of an entry from the KEGG PATHWAY database of pathway maps for molecular interactions and reaction networks.

format_1648.name: MetaCyc entry format
format_1648.definition: The format of an entry from the MetaCyc metabolic pathways database.

format_1649.definition: The format of a report from the HumanCyc metabolic pathways database.

format_1650.name: INOH entry format

format_1651.name: PATIKA entry format
format_1651.definition: The format of an entry from the PATIKA biological pathways database.

format_1652.name: Reactome entry format
format_1652.definition: The format of an entry from the reactome biological pathways database.

format_1653.name: aMAZE entry format
format_1653.definition: The format of an entry from the aMAZE biological pathways and molecular interactions database.

format_1654.name: CPDB entry format
format_1654.definition: The format of an entry from the CPDB database.

format_1655.name: Panther Pathways entry format
format_1655.definition: The format of an entry from the Panther Pathways database.

format_1666.definition:
Format of mathematical models from the BioModel database.
Models are annotated and linked to relevant data resources, such as publications, databases of compounds and pathways, controlled vocabularies, etc.

format_1697.name: KEGG LIGAND entry format
format_1697.definition: The format of an entry from the KEGG LIGAND chemical database.

format_1698.name: KEGG COMPOUND entry format
format_1698.definition: The format of an entry from the KEGG COMPOUND database.

format_1699.definition: The format of an entry from the KEGG PLANT database.

format_1700.definition: The format of an entry from the KEGG GLYCAN database.

format_1701.definition: The format of an entry from PubChem.

format_1702.name: ChemSpider entry format
format_1702.definition: The format of an entry from a database of chemical structures and property predictions.

format_1703.name: ChEBI entry format
format_1703.definition:
The format of an entry from Chemical Entities of Biological Interest (ChEBI).
ChEBI includes an ontological classification defining relations between entities or classes of entities.

format_1704.name: MSDchem ligand dictionary entry format
format_1704.definition: The format of an entry from the MSDchem ligand dictionary.

format_1705.name: HET group dictionary entry format
format_1705.definition: The format of an entry from the HET group dictionary (HET groups from PDB files).

format_1706.name: KEGG DRUG entry format
format_1706.definition: The format of an entry from the KEGG DRUG database.

format_1734.name: PubMed citation
format_1734.definition: Format of bibliographic reference as used by the PubMed database.

format_1735.definition:
Format for abstracts of scientific articles from the Medline database.
Bibliographic reference information including citation information is included

format_1736.name: CiteXplore-core
format_1736.definition: CiteXplore 'core' citation format including title, journal, authors and abstract.

format_1737.name: CiteXplore-all
format_1737.definition: CiteXplore 'all' citation format includes all known details such as Mesh terms and cross-references.

format_1739.name: pmc
format_1739.definition: Article format of the PubMed Central database.

format_1740.name: iHOP format
format_1740.definition: The format of iHOP (Information Hyperlinked over Proteins) text-mining result.

format_1741.name: OSCAR format
format_1741.definition:
OSCAR format of annotated chemical text.
OSCAR (Open-Source Chemistry Analysis Routines) software performs chemistry-specific parsing of chemical documents. It attempts to identify chemical names, ontology concepts, and chemical data from a document.

format_1747.name: PDB atom record format
format_1747.definition: Format of an ATOM record (describing data for an individual atom) from a PDB file.

format_1760.name: CATH chain report format
format_1760.definition:
Format of CATH domain classification information for a polypeptide chain.
The report (for example http://www.cathdb.info/chain/1cukA) includes chain identifiers, domain identifiers and CATH codes for domains in a given protein chain.

format_1761.name: CATH PDB report format
format_1761.definition:
Format of CATH domain classification information for a protein PDB file.
The report (for example http://www.cathdb.info/pdb/1cuk) includes chain identifiers, domain identifiers and CATH codes for domains in a given PDB file.

format_1782.name: NCBI gene report format
format_1782.definition: Entry (gene) format of the NCBI database.

format_1808.name: GeneIlluminator gene report format
format_1808.definition:
Report format for biological functions associated with a gene name and its alternative names (synonyms, homonyms), as generated by the GeneIlluminator service.
This includes a gene name and abbreviation of the name which may be in a name space indicating the gene status and relevant organisation.

format_1809.name: BacMap gene card format
format_1809.definition: Format of a report on the DNA and protein sequences for a given gene label from a bacterial chromosome maps from the BacMap database.

format_1810.name: ColiCard report format
format_1810.definition: Format of a report on Escherichia coli genes, proteins and molecules from the CyberCell Database (CCDB).

format_1861.name: PlasMapper TextMap
format_1861.definition: Map of a plasmid (circular DNA) in PlasMapper TextMap format.

format_1915.name: Format
format_1915.definition:
A defined way or layout of representing and structuring data in a computer file, blob, string, message, or elsewhere.
The main focus in EDAM lies on formats as means of structuring data exchanged between different tools or resources. The serialisation, compression, or encoding of concrete data formats/models is not in scope of EDAM. Format 'is format of' Data.

format_1918.name: Atomic data format
format_1918.definition: Data format for an individual atom.

format_1919.name: Sequence record format
format_1919.definition: Data format for a molecular sequence record.

format_1920.name: Sequence feature annotation format
format_1920.definition: Data format for molecular sequence feature information.

format_1921.name: Alignment format
format_1921.definition: Data format for molecular sequence alignment information.

format_1926.name: dbid

GCG sequence file format.

Genpept protein entry format.

format_1939.name: GFF3-seq

format_1947.name: GCG MSF

PDB sequence format (ATOM lines).

pdbnuc format in EMBOSS.

format_1952.name: pdbseqresnuc

PDB nucleotide sequence format (SEQRES lines).

format_1953.name: pdbseqres
format_1953.definition:
PDB sequence format (SEQRES lines).
pdbseq format in EMBOSS.

format_1954.name: Pearson format
format_1954.definition: Plain old FASTA sequence format (unspecified format for IDs).

format_1957.name: raw
format_1957.definition: Raw sequence format with no non-sequence characters.

format_1958.name: refseqp
format_1958.definition:
Refseq protein entry sequence format.
Currently identical to genpept format

format_1961.name: Stockholm format
format_1961.definition: Stockholm multiple sequence alignment format (used by Pfam and Rfam).

format_1968.name: dasdna
format_1968.definition:
DAS sequence (XML) format (nucleotide-only).

format_1969.name: debug-seq
format_1969.definition: EMBOSS debugging trace sequence format of full internal data content.

format_1972.name: NCBI format
format_1972.definition:
NCBI FASTA sequence format with NCBI-style IDs.
There are several variants of this.

format_1974.name: GFF2
format_1974.definition: General Feature Format (GFF) of sequence features.

format_1975.name: GFF3
format_1975.definition: Generic Feature Format version 3 (GFF3) of sequence features.

format_1979.name: debug-feat
format_1979.definition: EMBOSS debugging trace feature format of full internal data content.

format_1983.name: debug

format_1990.name: match

format_1999.name: scores format

format_2002.name: srs format

format_2003.name: srspair

format_2021.name: Text mining report format
format_2021.definition: Data format of a report from text mining.

format_2030.name: Chemical data format
format_2030.definition: Format of a report on a chemical compound.

format_2031.name: Gene annotation format

format_2034.definition: Data format for a biological model.

format_2035.definition: Text format of a chemical formula.

format_2038.definition: Format of phylogenetic discrete states data.

format_2045.definition: Annotation format for electron microscopy models.

format_2052.definition: Format for reports on a protein family.

format_2057.definition: Format for sequence trace data (i.e. including base call information).

format_2058.definition: Format of a file of gene expression data, e.g. a gene expression matrix or profile.

format_2059.definition: Format of a report on genotype / phenotype information.

format_2066.definition: Format of a report on sequence hits and associated data from searching a sequence database.

format_2067.name: Sequence distance matrix format
format_2067.definition: Format of a matrix of genetic distances between molecular sequences.

format_2072.name: Hidden Markov model format
format_2072.definition: Format of a hidden Markov model.

format_2074.name: Dirichlet distribution format
format_2074.definition: Data format of a dirichlet distribution.

format_2075.name: HMM emission and transition counts format
format_2075.definition: Data format for the emission and transition counts of a hidden Markov model.

format_2077.name: Protein secondary structure format

format_2078.name: Sequence range format
format_2078.definition: Format used to specify range(s) of sequence positions.

format_2094.name: pure

format_2095.name: unpure
format_2095.definition: Alphabet for a molecular sequence with possible unknown positions but possibly with non-sequence characters.

format_2096.name: unambiguous sequence
format_2096.definition: Alphabet for a molecular sequence with possible unknown positions but without ambiguity characters.

format_2097.name: ambiguous
format_2097.definition: Alphabet for a molecular sequence with possible unknown positions and possible ambiguity characters.

format_2155.name: Sequence features (repeats) format
format_2155.definition: Format used for map of repeats in molecular (typically nucleotide) sequences.

format_2158.name: Nucleic acid features (restriction sites) format

format_2159.name: Gene features (coding region) format
format_2159.definition: Format used for report on coding regions in nucleotide sequences.

format_2170.name: Sequence cluster format
format_2170.definition: Format used for clusters of molecular sequences.

format_2171.name: Sequence cluster format (protein)

format_2172.name: Sequence cluster format (nucleic acid)
format_2172.definition: Format used for clusters of nucleotide sequences.

format_2175.name: Gene cluster format
format_2175.definition: Format used for clusters of genes.

format_2181.name: EMBL-like (text)
format_2181.definition:
A text format resembling EMBL entry format.
This concept may be used for the many non-standard EMBL-like text formats.

format_2182.name: FASTQ-like format (text)
format_2182.definition:
A text format resembling FASTQ short read format.
This concept may be used for non-standard FASTQ short read-like formats.

format_2187.name: UniProt-like (text)
format_2187.definition: A text sequence format resembling uniprotkb entry format.

format_2194.name: medline
format_2194.definition: Abstract format used by MedLine database.

format_2196.name: OBO format
format_2196.definition: A serialisation format conforming to the Open Biomedical Ontologies (OBO) model.

format_2197.name: OWL format
format_2197.definition: A serialisation format conforming to the Web Ontology Language (OWL) model.

format_2200.name: FASTA-like (text)
format_2200.definition:
A text format resembling FASTA format.
This concept may also be used for the many non-standard FASTA-like formats.

format_2202.name: Sequence record full format
format_2202.definition: Data format for a molecular sequence record, typically corresponding to a full entry from a molecular sequence database.

format_2203.name: Sequence record lite format
format_2203.definition: Data format for a molecular sequence record 'lite', typically molecular sequence and minimal metadata, such as an identifier of the sequence and/or a comment.

format_2204.name: EMBL format (XML)
format_2204.definition:
An XML format for EMBL entries.
This is a placeholder for other more specific concepts. It should not normally be used for annotation.

format_2205.name: GenBank-like format (text)
format_2205.definition:
A text format resembling GenBank entry (plain text) format.
This concept may be used for the non-standard GenBank-like text formats.

format_2206.name: Sequence feature table format (text)
